1
00:00:02,236 --> 00:00:04,102
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.    
    WHO AM I?                   


2
00:00:04,171 --> 00:00:06,305
WAS I BOUGHT? STOLEN?           
WHERE ARE MY MOM AND DAD?       


3
00:00:06,373 --> 00:00:08,940
    - THIS IS MY MOTHER.        
    -<i> [ Sydney ] YES, IT IS.</i>    


4
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:11,676
<i>HIS NAME IS ANGELO.</i>             


5
00:00:11,745 --> 00:00:16,248
<i>SOMEONE WHO CAN ABSORB THE</i>      
<i>INTELLECTUAL, EMOTIONAL, EVEN</i>   
<i>THE PHYSICAL TRAITS OF OTHERS...</i>


6
00:00:16,316 --> 00:00:18,016
<i>AND LITERALLY BECOMES</i>           
<i>THAT PERSON.</i>                    


7
00:00:18,085 --> 00:00:21,120
- I WANT TO KNOW                
  WHAT HAPPENED TO MY MOTHER.   
- I KILLED HER.                 


8
00:00:21,188 --> 00:00:23,222
THAT'S WHAT I                   
TORTURE MYSELF BELIEVING.       


9
00:00:23,290 --> 00:00:28,527
<i>RAINES IS A DANGEROUS MAN. HE</i>   
<i>MAY BE INVOLVED WITH THE MURDER</i> 
<i>OF MISS PARKER'S MOTHER.</i>        


10
00:00:28,596 --> 00:00:31,663
<i>- I FANTASIZE ABOUT KILLING HIM.</i>
<i>- THE ONLY PEOPLE WHO KNOW</i>      
<i>  ABOUT SL 27...</i>                


11
00:00:31,732 --> 00:00:33,531
ARE EITHER DEAD                 
OR COMATOSE.                    


12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,568
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>SL 27. SUBLEVEL 27.</i>             


13
00:00:36,637 --> 00:00:38,903
    <i> - WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?</i>   
     - BIRTHING TABLE.          


14
00:00:38,972 --> 00:00:40,605
            WITH SHACKLES?      


15
00:00:45,479 --> 00:00:47,479
<i>[ Gate Buzzes ]</i>                 


16
00:00:49,216 --> 00:00:53,618
<i>[ Chatter, Indistinct ]</i>         


17
00:00:53,687 --> 00:00:57,022
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>YOU GOT MY RADIO OR WHAT?</i>       


18
00:01:08,869 --> 00:01:11,703
            <i> YOU KNOW THE DRILL.</i>


19
00:01:24,384 --> 00:01:27,886
BETTER TIGHTEN THEM SHACKLES.   
            HOUDINI COULDN'T    
            GET OUT OF THESE.   


20
00:01:27,955 --> 00:01:30,955
TIGHTEN 'EM.                    
    WHY? THIS CONVICT'S NOT     
    PLAYING WITH A FULL DECK?   


21
00:01:31,024 --> 00:01:34,526
    DECK AND A HALF, BROTHER.   
    ALL WILD CARDS.             


22
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:37,128
BIT A GUARD'S NOSE OFF ONCE.    
SAID HE DIDN'T LIKE THE WAY...  


23
00:01:37,198 --> 00:01:40,065
THE GUARD USED IT               
TO LOOK DOWN ON HIM.            
                    [ Scoffs ]  


24
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:42,835
        <i> A LITTLE REEDUCATION</i>   
        <i> WILL CHANGE HIS DIET.</i>  


25
00:01:42,903 --> 00:01:46,805
    <i> SIGNED, SEALED</i>             
    <i> AND SOON TO BE DELIVERED.</i>  


26
00:01:46,873 --> 00:01:48,840
[ Coughing ]                    
            HEY, HEY.           


27
00:01:52,313 --> 00:01:55,647
    LIKE I SAID. WILD CARDS.    


28
00:01:55,715 --> 00:01:58,716
        [ Grunting ]            


29
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:02,454
        THAT'S A TASTE OF       
        YOUR FUTURE. COME ON.   


30
00:02:11,264 --> 00:02:15,033
    NOW, REMEMBER,              
    ALWAYS IRRIGATE YOUR GUMS.  


31
00:02:15,102 --> 00:02:18,637
    I AQUA-FLUSH EVERY NIGHT.   
                GOOD. WHAT ABOUT
                YOUR BROTHER?   


32
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:20,805
        HE DOESN'T EVEN FLOSS.  


33
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:22,774
        IKE, CAN I HAVE         
        MY SUCKER, PLEASE?      


34
00:02:25,779 --> 00:02:30,782
THANK YOU. WE TRY WITH HIM,     
DR. JAROD, BUT I GUESS IKE      
WILL ALWAYS BE A GOOFUS.        


35
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:34,986
        - A GOOFUS?             
        - AND GALLANT.          
          IT'S ALL IN HERE.     


36
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:43,561
"GOOFUS LEAVES HIS ROOM         
 A MESS. GALLANT MAKES HIS BED  
 EVERY DAY."                    


37
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:47,132
    <i> A MORALITY LESSON</i>          
    <i> IN A CHILDREN'S COMIC BOOK.</i>
    <i> FASCINATING.</i>               


38
00:02:47,201 --> 00:02:50,401
    - [ Burps ]                 
    - I'LL HAVE TO READ THESE.  


39
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:53,538
<i>[ Woman On TV ]</i>                 
<i>THE CONVICTS TOOK CONTROL</i>       
<i>OF THE TRANSPORT VAN.</i>           


40
00:02:53,607 --> 00:02:58,343
MOMENTS AGO, I SPOKE WITH       
THE PRISON GUARDS LUCKY         
TO HAVE SURVIVED.               


41
00:02:58,412 --> 00:03:02,046
ALL OF A SUDDEN, HE WAS IN      
THE CAB. THOUGHT HE WAS GONNA   
KILL US RIGHT THERE.            


42
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:04,983
    COOL.                       
<i>HE KEPT SMILING AT US,</i>          


43
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:07,218
<i>LIKE HE WAS HAVING FUN</i>          
<i>MESSING WITH OUR MINDS.</i>         


44
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:10,689
HE LOCKED US IN THE BACK OF     
THE VAN, DROVE INTO THE POND.   


45
00:03:10,758 --> 00:03:13,859
ONLY AN INCH OF AIR TO BREATHE. 
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA DIE.      


46
00:03:13,927 --> 00:03:17,562
THE F.B.I. TASK FORCE, LED BY   
SPECIAL AGENT KORKOS,           


47
00:03:17,631 --> 00:03:21,533
IS ON THE TRAIL OF              
THIS CRIMINAL,                  
KNOWN ONLY AS JOHN DOE.         


48
00:03:21,602 --> 00:03:26,037
<i>THE ESCAPEE IS 6'1",</i>            
<i>175 POUNDS...</i>                   


49
00:03:26,106 --> 00:03:29,240
AND HAS A DISTINCTIVE BURN MARK 
ON HIS RIGHT HAND.              


50
00:03:29,309 --> 00:03:33,011
<i>WE'LL HAVE MORE ON</i>              
<i>THIS BREAKING STORY AS</i>          
<i>INFORMATION BECOMES AVAILABLE.</i>  


51
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:37,582
    COOL.                       
            HE'S INCORRIGIBLE,  
            DR. JAROD.          


52
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:40,051
                DR. JAROD?      


53
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:43,722
    - YOU HAVE TO TALK.         
    - NO.                       


54
00:03:45,525 --> 00:03:49,894
WHY? THE ANTICIPATION OF PAIN   
IS CLEARLY MORE EFFECTIVE       
THAN THE PAIN ITSELF.           


55
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:54,165
- HE'S ALMOST AT THE BRINK.     
- [ Young Raines ] DON'T ARGUE  
  WITH ME, JUST DO IT.          


56
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:57,035
            BUT--               
JUST DO IT.                     


57
00:04:00,641 --> 00:04:04,776
    - OW! YOU BURNT MY HAND!    
    - IT WAS REAL, SYDNEY!      


58
00:04:04,845 --> 00:04:06,844
            YOU BASTARD!        
    SWEEPERS.                   


59
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:09,581
GET TO THE INFIRMARY NOW.       


60
00:04:09,649 --> 00:04:11,950
        KYLE, I'M SORRY!        
        I WOULD NEVER HURT YOU. 


61
00:04:12,019 --> 00:04:16,855
KYLE, I WOULD NEVER HURT YOU.   
I WOULD NEVER HURT YOU. KYLE.   


62
00:04:16,924 --> 00:04:18,890
            NEVER HURT YOU.     


63
00:04:25,032 --> 00:04:28,533
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


64
00:05:14,247 --> 00:05:16,581
IN ALL THE TIME THAT            
HE'S BEEN HERE, DID YOU         
INTERACT WITH HIM?              


65
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:18,816
OH, YEAH, WE INTERACTED,        
BUT IT WASN'T ALWAYS HIM.       


66
00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:21,552
HE ALWAYS THOUGHT               
HE WAS SOMEBODY DIFFERENT       
EVERY TIME YOU SEE HIM.         


67
00:05:21,621 --> 00:05:23,621
COULD TALK WITH A DOCTOR,       
ASTRONAUT, ANYTHING.            


68
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:26,692
    YEAH, SO WHAT DO YOU        
    CRIMINAL PSYCHOLOGISTS      
    CALL THAT ANYWAY?           


69
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:30,428
MULTIPLE PERSONALITIES?         
        SOMETHING LIKE THAT.    


70
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:33,999
WEIRD TOO, MAN. I MEAN,         
THIS GUY SPENDS 10 YEARS        
IN STIR,                        


71
00:05:34,068 --> 00:05:37,235
AND NOBODY COULD FIGURE OUT     
WHO HE WAS, WHERE HE COME FROM. 


72
00:05:37,304 --> 00:05:40,038
IS THAT WHY                     
YOU CALLED HIM "JOHN DOE"?      
                    YEAH.       


73
00:05:40,106 --> 00:05:42,474
<i>I ACTUALLY BELIEVE THIS GUY</i>     
<i>DIDN'T KNOW WHO HE WAS EITHER.</i>  


74
00:05:42,542 --> 00:05:47,546
HE USED TO TELL ME THERE WAS    
VOICES SPEAKING TO HIM          
IN HIS HEAD ALL THE TIME.       


75
00:05:47,614 --> 00:05:52,116
IN THIS GUY'S CASE,             
THEM VOICES WERE REALLY THERE.  


76
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:56,287
<i>AND WHEN THOSE VOICES TOLD HIM</i>  
<i>HE WAS SOMEBODY DIFFERENT,</i>      
<i>HE MADE YOU BELIEVE IT TOO.</i>     


77
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:00,424
            REALLY?             


78
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:02,794
    I REMEMBER ONE TIME         
     I PLAYED ALONG WITH HIM.   


79
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:06,130
        <i> HE TOLD ME HE WAS</i>      
        <i> AN I.R.S. INVESTIGATOR.</i>


80
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:12,003
    <i> SO I LET HIM DO MY TAXES.</i>  
    <i> THE GUY GOT ME</i>             
    <i> A $4,000 REFUND.</i>           


81
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:28,286
    HEY. I ALWAYS WONDERED      
    WHERE HE KEPT THAT THING.   


82
00:06:28,354 --> 00:06:32,523
HE USED TO SIT THERE, SCRIBBLING
IN THAT THING LIKE A MADMAN     
EVERY TIME HIS DOCTOR LEFT.     


83
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:40,097
    <i> - WHAT'S IT SAY?</i>           
    <i> - THAT HE'S DANGEROUS.</i>     


84
00:06:40,166 --> 00:06:43,001
WHAT WAS HIS DOCTOR'S NAME?     


85
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:45,570
    I CALLED HIM "DR. WHEEZY."  


86
00:06:45,638 --> 00:06:49,640
    NOT POLITE I KNOW, BUT HEY, 
    THE GUY, HE BREATHED FUNNY. 


87
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:53,978
    I GUESS ANYBODY WOULD,      
    DRAGGING AROUND HIS OWN     
    OXYGEN TANK THOUGH, HUH?    


88
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:57,214
<i>[ Buzzing ]</i>                     


89
00:07:11,398 --> 00:07:14,899
[ Sydney ]                      
WE'RE GIVING ANGELO EVERY       
RED NOTEBOOK JAROD EVER MADE.   


90
00:07:14,968 --> 00:07:19,971
<i>[ Miss Parker ] NOW TELL ME</i>     
<i>AGAIN: EXACTLY WHAT'S BUZZ BOY</i>  
<i>GOING TO DO WITH THEM?</i>          


91
00:07:20,039 --> 00:07:23,908
<i>[ Broots ] THE THEORY IS THAT</i>   
<i>SINCE ANGELO CAN ABSORB ALL THE</i> 
<i>PERSONALITY DATA GIVEN TO HIM...</i>


92
00:07:23,977 --> 00:07:29,314
    MAYBE, JUST MAYBE,          
    HE MIGHT BE ABLE TO         
    DETERMINE WHERE JAROD IS... 


93
00:07:29,382 --> 00:07:33,017
EMOTIONALLY AND PHYSICALLY.     


94
00:07:33,086 --> 00:07:38,255
WELL, THEN, LET'S SEE           
WHAT THE POTATO HEAD CAN DO.    


95
00:07:38,324 --> 00:07:40,258
                OKAY.           


96
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:51,069
        PUT IT DOWN, ANGELO.    


97
00:07:53,406 --> 00:07:56,374
    PUT HIM BACK IN HIS SPACE.  


98
00:07:56,443 --> 00:07:58,743
            I HAVE AUTHORIZATION
            TO USE HIM.         


99
00:08:00,747 --> 00:08:05,383
NO ONE BELOW ME                 
CAN AUTHORIZE HIS USE.          


100
00:08:05,452 --> 00:08:08,886
    MY FATHER ISN'T BELOW YOU.  


101
00:08:25,038 --> 00:08:27,973
THIS BETTER WORK.               


102
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:30,041
    WELL, I KNOW IF IT DOESN'T, 
    MY BUTT'S ON THE LINE.      


103
00:08:30,109 --> 00:08:33,444
MMM, WRONG PIECE                
OF ANATOMY.                     


104
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:48,460
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>                 


105
00:08:50,563 --> 00:08:55,232
HELLO. THIS IS HARRIET.         


106
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:08,412
    SOMEBODY OPEN A WINDOW.     
    IT STINKS IN HERE.          


107
00:09:08,481 --> 00:09:10,648
DO WE HAVE POINT OF ORIGIN      
ON THAT PHONE CALL YET?         


108
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,784
<i>A FRIEND CALLED</i>                 
<i>TO WARN HARRIET TASHMAN</i>         
<i>ABOUT THE ESCAPED JOHN DOE.</i>     


109
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:16,320
<i>THEY TRACED THE CALL</i>            
<i>AT LOCAL HEADQUARTERS</i>           
<i>WHEN I GOT THERE.</i>               


110
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:20,691
SPECIAL AGENT JAROD NESS.       
I WAS SENT BY WASHINGTON.       


111
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:23,194
        - NESS?                 
        - NO RELATION.          


112
00:09:23,263 --> 00:09:26,264
    [ Chuckles ] WELL, WELCOME  
    ABOARD. WE NEED ALL THE HELP
    WE CAN GET ON THIS ONE.     


113
00:09:26,332 --> 00:09:29,701
    <i> THE ESCAPEE IS A JOHN DOE.</i> 


114
00:09:29,769 --> 00:09:32,336
IN THE 10 YEARS SINCE           
HIS ARREST, WE COULDN'T FIND    
ANYTHING ABOUT HIM.             


115
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:35,873
    NO PRIORS. NO FINGERPRINT   
    MATCHES, D.N.A., NOTHING.   


116
00:09:35,942 --> 00:09:40,278
LIKE HE FELL FROM THE SKY.      
HE WAS CONVICTED OF A STRING    
OF VIOLENT FELONIES...          


117
00:09:40,347 --> 00:09:44,515
ON A CROSS-COUNTRY BINGE        
THAT ENDED IN THE KIDNAPPING    
OF ONE HARRIET TASHMAN...       


118
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:48,252
WHOSE SPILLED SOUP              
YOU HAPPEN TO BE STANDING IN.   


119
00:09:48,321 --> 00:09:50,888
ALL OF THOSE VICTIMS            
SHARED ONE COMMON DENOMINATOR.  


120
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:55,693
THEY WERE ALL TERRIFIED.        
THIS SICK PUPPY RELISHES        
PSYCHOLOGICAL TORTURE.          


121
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:59,997
DOE STALKED MISS TASHMAN        
FOR TWO DAYS BEFORE             
HE GRABBED HER AT GUNPOINT...   


122
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:02,066
AND FORCED HER                  
TO DRIVE HIM AWAY.              


123
00:10:02,135 --> 00:10:05,803
MISS TASHMAN HAD                
THE PRESENCE OF MIND TO CRASH   
THE CAR INTO AN EMBANKMENT,     


124
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:09,807
INJURING HERSELF AND JOHN DOE,  
BUT THEREBY ESCAPING WHATEVER   
FATE HE HAD IN STORE FOR HER.   


125
00:10:09,876 --> 00:10:14,044
    <i> - THAT WAS 10 YEARS AGO.</i>   
     - AND YOU THINK            
       HE'S AFTER HER AGAIN?    


126
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:17,114
<i>IT'S SPECULATION ON MY PART,</i>    
<i>BUT ALL OF THOSE ACTIONS...</i>     


127
00:10:17,183 --> 00:10:19,184
<i>PRIOR TO HER KIDNAP</i>             
<i>WERE RANDOM.</i>                    


128
00:10:19,252 --> 00:10:22,887
<i>HE CAME HERE FOR HER,</i>           
<i>AND, CLEARLY, HE WAS</i>            
<i>TAKING HER SOMEWHERE.</i>           


129
00:10:22,956 --> 00:10:27,459
ARE WE SURE HE WAS AFTER HER?   
HE WAS BEFORE, AND BY THE LOOK  
OF HOW QUICKLY SHE LEFT,        


130
00:10:27,527 --> 00:10:30,361
        HE MUST BE AGAIN.       
                AREN'T YOU GUYS 
                DONE YET?       


131
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:33,231
                    WHO ARE YOU?
JENKINS. I'M THE MANAGER        
OF THIS PLACE.                  


132
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:36,201
    <i> NESS, TAKE MR. JENKINS'S</i>   
    <i> STATEMENT.</i>                 


133
00:10:36,269 --> 00:10:38,536
<i>OH, COME ON.</i>                    
<i>I GAVE A STATEMENT</i>              
<i>TO THE FIRST GUY.</i>               


134
00:10:38,605 --> 00:10:42,206
    - THE FIRST GUY?            
    - THE F.B.I. AGENT WHO WAS  
      HERE THIS MORNING.        


135
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:47,278
<i>[ Dog Barking In Distance ]</i>     


136
00:10:59,793 --> 00:11:04,629
- YEAH, YEAH. WHERE TO?         
- PERFECT DAY LIKE THIS,        
  I'LL TELL YOU WHEN TO STOP.   


137
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:07,365
        <i> HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.</i>    
        <i> NO SMOKING.</i>            


138
00:11:07,434 --> 00:11:09,767
        YOU MEAN ME?            


139
00:11:09,836 --> 00:11:13,037
<i>NO. I MEAN THE INVISIBLE GUY</i>    
<i>NEXT TO YOU. YEAH, YOU.</i>         
<i>PUT IT OUT.</i>                     


140
00:11:13,106 --> 00:11:15,940
    BUT I JUST LIT IT.          
            <i> I DON'T CARE IF</i>    
            <i> YOU INVENTED IT.</i>   


141
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:17,308
        PUT IT OUT.             


142
00:11:20,947 --> 00:11:22,947
        WHATEVER YOU SAY.       


143
00:11:28,955 --> 00:11:33,791
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>CALM DOWN, MISS PARKER.</i>         
<i>YOU'VE GOT TO HAVE PATIENCE.</i>    


144
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:37,362
    <i> PATIENCE? DON'T TALK TO ME</i> 
    <i> ABOUT PATIENCE.</i>            


145
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:42,100
WHAT I NEED IS A CATTLE PROD.   
MAYBE THAT'LL JUMP-START        
THE LITTLE LAB RAT.             


146
00:11:45,738 --> 00:11:49,907
<i>HE HASN'T BLINKED, SMILED,</i>      
<i>MOVED, NOTHING.</i>                 


147
00:11:49,976 --> 00:11:55,646
<i>ANGELO IS ABSORBING</i>             
<i>HIS WAY THROUGH</i>                 
<i>THE NOTEBOOKS CHRONOLOGICALLY.</i>  


148
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:58,883
<i>RIGHT NOW, HE'S IN</i>              
<i>THE MID-'70s.</i>                   


149
00:11:58,952 --> 00:12:01,452
<i>I BELIEVE I SAW HIM SQUINT</i>      
<i>AROUND 1969.</i>                    


150
00:12:01,521 --> 00:12:05,023
<i>[ Broots ] AFTER LOOKING AT</i>     
<i>THE NOTEBOOK ON MARILYN MONROE,</i> 
<i>I THINK HE GIGGLED.</i>             


151
00:12:07,427 --> 00:12:10,195
        I SHOULD NEVER HAVE     
        PUT MYSELF ON THE LINE  
        FOR YOU TWO.            


152
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:12,197
            <i> THIS IS A WASTE</i>    
            <i> OF TIME, SYD.</i>      


153
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:23,107
            <i> [ Angelo Growling ]</i>


154
00:12:26,279 --> 00:12:29,147
<i>[ Miss Parker Choking ]</i>         


155
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:31,182
        <i> - ANGELO, NO.</i>          
         - SAM, HELP!           


156
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:33,951
LET GO OF HER, ANGELO.          
ANGELO, LET GO.                 


157
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:36,220
<i>SWEEPERS, HELP!</i>                 


158
00:12:36,289 --> 00:12:38,790
<i>ANGELO, LET GO!</i>                 


159
00:12:42,662 --> 00:12:46,998
    - MISS PARKER, YOU OKAY?    
    - [ Panting ]               


160
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:49,733
    YOU OKAY?                   
        WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT? 


161
00:12:49,802 --> 00:12:54,172
A VIOLENT REACTION TO           
WHATEVER WAS IN                 
THE RED NOTEBOOK.               


162
00:12:56,276 --> 00:12:59,143
                IT'S NOT RED.   


163
00:12:59,212 --> 00:13:03,414
        <i> THE NOTEBOOK HE WAS</i>    
        <i> ABSORBING, IT'S BLUE.</i>  


164
00:13:03,483 --> 00:13:06,317
<i>[ Phones Ringing ]</i>              


165
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:52,363
<i>[ Woman ] RESIDENTS WERE</i>        
<i>STUNNED BY THE ATTACK ON</i>        
<i>HARRIET TASHMAN, A FORMER NUN.</i>  


166
00:13:52,432 --> 00:13:54,732
TASHMAN'S INJURIES WERE MINOR,  


167
00:13:54,801 --> 00:13:57,768
AND SOURCES REPORT THAT SHE     
DOES NOT WANT TO PRESS CHARGES. 


168
00:13:57,837 --> 00:14:01,172
AT THE MOMENT, A SPOKESPERSON   
FOR THE POLICE IS TELLING US... 


169
00:14:01,241 --> 00:14:04,408
THAT THEY ARE CONSIDERING       
THIS CASE CLOSED.               


170
00:14:12,485 --> 00:14:14,418
            OH, MY GOD.         


171
00:14:16,889 --> 00:14:20,157
    <i> [ Drawer Opens, Closes ]</i>   


172
00:14:28,901 --> 00:14:30,835
                MOM.            


173
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:41,845
                HE SCARED ME.   


174
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:47,218
            I'M GLAD            
            HE DIDN'T HURT YOU. 


175
00:14:47,287 --> 00:14:50,454
        ANGELO HAS ALWAYS BEEN  
        A MYSTERY.              


176
00:14:52,792 --> 00:14:54,792
        SOMETHING ON YOUR MIND? 


177
00:14:54,861 --> 00:14:58,229
    MR. RAINES WAS UPSET THAT   
    I GAVE YOU ACCESS TO ANGELO.


178
00:14:58,297 --> 00:15:00,731
BOOHOO FOR DRACULA.             


179
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,801
ANGELO IS HIS PROJECT.          


180
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:06,638
APPARENTLY, RAINES HAS BEEN     
WORRIED ABOUT HIM               
BECOMING VIOLENT.               


181
00:15:06,706 --> 00:15:09,974
    THE GUY IS A MARSHMALLOW.   
<i>STILL, HE ATTACKED YOU.</i>         


182
00:15:10,043 --> 00:15:13,977
THAT JUSTIFIES RAINES'S FEAR    
AND CONCERN FOR YOU.            
                    <i> CONCERN?</i>   


183
00:15:14,046 --> 00:15:19,784
DADDY, YOU MAY NOT WANT TO      
HEAR THIS, BUT I THINK          
HE'S WORKING BEHIND YOUR BACK.  


184
00:15:19,853 --> 00:15:23,487
HE WOULD NOT DEFY ME.           


185
00:15:28,828 --> 00:15:32,162
        I'M SORRY. DADDY,       
        I KNOW THAT THAT TONE   
        IS INAPPROPRIATE.       


186
00:15:32,231 --> 00:15:35,232
NO, NO, NO. YOU MAY BE RIGHT.   


187
00:15:35,301 --> 00:15:38,969
I'VE NEVER DOUBTED              
RAINES'S DEDICATION,            
BUT HE'S BEEN DIFFERENT.        


188
00:15:39,038 --> 00:15:44,041
    EVER SINCE JAROD'S BEEN OUT,
    I'VE WONDERED IF            
    THERE WAS SOMETHING.        


189
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:46,143
TRUST ME, DADDY.                
THERE IS.                       


190
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,948
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING TANGIBLE?  


191
00:15:52,318 --> 00:15:54,184
            NO.                 


192
00:15:54,253 --> 00:15:59,490
IF YOU SHOULD FIND SOMETHING    
REAL, SOMETHING I COULD TRUST-- 


193
00:15:59,559 --> 00:16:03,327
I'LL BRING IT                   
TO YOUR ATTENTION IMMEDIATELY.  


194
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:43,201
            MY GRANDPA WAS      
            THE CARETAKER HERE  
            BEFORE ME.          


195
00:16:43,269 --> 00:16:46,604
MISS HARRIET, SHE'S THE WOMAN   
WHO OWNS THIS PLACE,            


196
00:16:46,673 --> 00:16:49,507
            GAVE ME THE JOB     
            AFTER GRANDPA DIED. 


197
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:55,646
        SHE SENDS ME MONEY      
        IN THE MAIL TO KEEP IT  
        LOOKING PRETTY FOR HER. 


198
00:16:55,715 --> 00:16:57,548
                FUNNY, HUH?     


199
00:16:57,616 --> 00:17:03,053
    FUNNY?                      
        WELL, THAT SHE WANTS IT 
        KEPT LOOKING SO PRETTY. 


200
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:05,623
        SHE AIN'T BEEN HERE     
        IN 10 YEARS OR MORE.    


201
00:17:07,126 --> 00:17:10,460
    DO YOU KNOW WHERE           
    SHE IS? HOW TO REACH HER?   


202
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:14,698
NO. I HAVEN'T TALKED            
WITH HER OR ANYTHING.           


203
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:19,103
SOMETIMES-- SOMETIMES           
I WONDER IF IT'S REALLY HER     
THAT SENDS THE MONEY.           


204
00:17:22,909 --> 00:17:25,276
        HAVE YOU EVER SEEN      
        THIS WOMAN BEFORE?      


205
00:17:28,014 --> 00:17:30,848
            I HAVE TO GO.       
JOE BILL, PLEASE.               


206
00:17:30,917 --> 00:17:34,752
THIS IS MY MOTHER.              
I DON'T KNOW WHERE SHE IS.      


207
00:17:36,589 --> 00:17:38,523
            NEVER KNEW MY MAMA. 


208
00:17:40,393 --> 00:17:43,728
            ALL THERE EVER WAS  
            WAS ME AND GRANDPA. 


209
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:50,568
    HE SAYS WE'RE NOT           
    SUPPOSED TO TALK ABOUT THEM.


210
00:17:50,637 --> 00:17:52,803
    THAT THEY DON'T LIVE HERE.  


211
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:57,909
THEY LIVED HERE?                
                OVER THE BARN.  


212
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:04,247
ALMOST NEVER CAME OUT.          
ALWAYS ALONE.                   


213
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:10,421
SHE HAD RED HAIR,               


214
00:18:10,489 --> 00:18:14,725
AND HE MADE PLANES OUT OF WOOD. 


215
00:18:14,793 --> 00:18:16,760
ALWAYS PLANES.                  


216
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:22,333
WHEN I WAS LITTLE,              
MISS HARRIET, SHE TAUGHT ME     
HOW TO READ GOOD-- GOODER.      


217
00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:25,403
THESE PEOPLE                    
ALWAYS SEEMED LIKE...           


218
00:18:25,471 --> 00:18:30,808
THAT BOOK ABOUT                 
THE LITTLE GIRL                 
WHO LIVED IN THE ATTIC.         


219
00:18:32,812 --> 00:18:36,980
HER NAME WAS ANNE.              


220
00:18:37,049 --> 00:18:39,383
                ANNE FRANK?     


221
00:18:40,886 --> 00:18:44,788
        THE FAMILY THAT WAS     
        HIDING FROM THE NAZIS.  
HIDING.                         


222
00:18:44,857 --> 00:18:47,190
        HIDING.                 


223
00:18:50,863 --> 00:18:54,598
<i>THEY LEFT RIGHT AFTER</i>           
<i>MISS HARRIET GOT TOOK.</i>          


224
00:18:54,666 --> 00:18:57,834
    MAYBE IT'S THEM             
    THAT SENDS THE MONEY, HUH?  


225
00:18:57,903 --> 00:19:01,672
    JOE BILL, DO YOU KNOW       
    WHERE THEY WENT?            


226
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:06,277
    JUST WENT.                  
    THEY LEFT SOME STUFF.       


227
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:11,849
<i>[ Cell Phone Rings ]</i>            


228
00:19:13,353 --> 00:19:16,186
                    YES.        
    THIS IS AGENT MEADOW.       
    WE GOT A LEAD ON DOE.       


229
00:19:16,255 --> 00:19:20,424
KORKOS WANTS EVERYONE           
HERE NOW. NESS. NESS?           


230
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:23,828
     - I'M ON MY WAY.           
    <i> - [ Phone Beeps Off ]</i>      


231
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:29,166
- I'LL BE BACK.                 
- CABBIE'S IN COUNTY GENERAL    
  PSYCH WARD.                   


232
00:19:29,234 --> 00:19:31,569
    NO INJURIES,                
    BUT MASSIVE SHOCK.          


233
00:19:31,637 --> 00:19:34,805
DOC SAYS HE WAS LITERALLY       
SCARED NEARLY TO DEATH.         
                WHAT HAPPENED?  


234
00:19:34,874 --> 00:19:38,041
HE WAS TIED INTO HIS SEAT.      
MOUTH TAPED SHUT.               
EYES TAPED OPEN.                


235
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:41,278
LIKE HE WANTED HIM              
TO WATCH SOMETHING.             
                    HIS FATE.   


236
00:19:41,347 --> 00:19:44,515
    DOE PARKED HIS CAB ON TOP   
    OF SOME RAILROAD TRACKS     
    FACING A TUNNEL.            


237
00:19:44,584 --> 00:19:46,917
<i>DID THE CABBIE</i>                  
<i>GIVE US ANY LEADS?</i>              


238
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:50,320
IT'S HARD TO TALK AFTER         
SOME PSYCHO'S PUT HIS CIGARETTE 
OUT ON YOUR TONGUE.             


239
00:19:50,389 --> 00:19:55,392
BUT HE DID SAY SOMETHING ABOUT  
DOE REPEATING, "I DECIDE        
WHO LIVES OR DIES."             


240
00:19:55,461 --> 00:19:58,462
    ALL THE MORE REASON         
    FOR US TO FIND HIM BEFORE   
    HE FINDS HARRIET TASHMAN--  


241
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:01,898
        IF HE HASN'T ALREADY.   


242
00:20:01,967 --> 00:20:05,635
<i>THIS BLUE NOTEBOOK</i>              
<i>BELONGED TO ANOTHER SUBJECT.</i>    


243
00:20:05,704 --> 00:20:09,439
HIS NAME'S KYLE, AND HE WAS     
PART OF THE PRETENDER PROGRAM   
HERE YEARS AGO...               


244
00:20:09,508 --> 00:20:13,610
        UNDER THE DIRECTION OF  
        THEN DR. RAINES.        


245
00:20:13,679 --> 00:20:18,683
I GUESS IT ONLY MAKES SENSE THAT
YOU'D HAVE MORE THAN ONE FREAK  
IN YOUR FARM SYSTEM.            


246
00:20:18,751 --> 00:20:20,584
WHAT MAKES KYLE SO SPECIAL?     


247
00:20:20,653 --> 00:20:23,987
            THE FACT THAT HE WAS
            OFFICIALLY RELEASED 
            FROM THE CENTER...  


248
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:26,690
        BEFORE THE DATE         
        ON THE BLUE NOTEBOOK.   


249
00:20:26,758 --> 00:20:31,995
        ARE YOU SAYING THAT     
        RAINES KEPT KYLE FOR    
        HIS OWN PROJECT? WHERE? 


250
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,701
        SL 27.                  


251
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:44,274
    I REROUTED                  
    THE SECURITY SYSTEM,        


252
00:20:44,343 --> 00:20:48,179
SO IF ANYONE HAS THIS PLACE     
MONITORED, IT SHOULD BE         
ALL RIGHT FOR ABOUT 30 MINUTES. 


253
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,180
LOOK, SINCE WE DON'T HAVE       
MUCH TIME...                    


254
00:20:50,248 --> 00:20:54,451
WHY DON'T YOU KEEP              
YOUR MOUTH SHUT                 
AND YOUR EYES OPEN.             


255
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:59,223
FINE WITH ME.                   
I DON'T WANNA BE                
DOWN HERE IN THE FIRST PLACE.   


256
00:20:59,292 --> 00:21:01,625
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>OVER HERE.</i>                      


257
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,968
        MY GOD.                 


258
00:21:11,037 --> 00:21:14,038
        SOMEBODY WAS FORCED     
        TO LIVE HERE.           


259
00:21:14,107 --> 00:21:16,440
            AND FROM THE LOOK OF
            THESE STRIATIONS,   


260
00:21:16,509 --> 00:21:21,678
    HE SPENT A GREAT DEAL       
    OF TIME TRYING TO           
    CLAW HIS WAY OUT OF HERE.   


261
00:21:23,849 --> 00:21:27,418
<i>SYDNEY. MISS PARKER.</i>            


262
00:21:27,486 --> 00:21:30,988
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>BROOTS, WHERE ARE YOU?</i>          
<i>DOWN HERE. DOWN THE HALL.</i>       


263
00:21:37,162 --> 00:21:40,130
                    WHAT IS IT? 
IT'S A BRAINCHILD.              


264
00:21:40,199 --> 00:21:43,033
ONE OF THE FIRST GENERATION     
OF SUPER COMPUTERS.             


265
00:21:43,101 --> 00:21:48,772
    RAINES'S BRAINCHILD.        
    THIS IS WHAT HE USED TO     
    RECORD HIS WORK DOWN HERE.  


266
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:53,043
<i>I HAD A COMPUTER LIKE THIS</i>      
<i>IN MY EARLY YEARS WITH JAROD.</i>   


267
00:21:53,112 --> 00:21:57,347
AND THIS WAS WHAT               
WE STORED HIS SIMS ON...        


268
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:59,783
BEFORE TRANSFERRING THEM        
TO D.S.A.                       


269
00:21:59,851 --> 00:22:02,386
<i>PRETTY USELESS NOW.</i>             


270
00:22:05,558 --> 00:22:10,393
UNLESS... THOSE ANALOGS         
WERE BACKED UP.                 


271
00:22:13,566 --> 00:22:19,069
                IN THERE? HOW?  
SOME OF THESE SYSTEMS HAD       
PRIMITIVE HARD-DRIVE MEMORIES.  


272
00:22:19,137 --> 00:22:24,141
[ Laughs ]                      
COMPUTER CLUB IN COLLEGE.       
            [ Forced Chuckle ]  


273
00:22:24,209 --> 00:22:26,876
            DO WHATEVER IT IS   
            YOU HAVE TO DO.     


274
00:22:26,946 --> 00:22:29,513
            IF IT'S IN THERE,   
            I WANT IT OUT.      


275
00:22:29,582 --> 00:22:32,682
    CALL ME WHEN YOU HAVE IT.   
WHOA, WHOA. WHOA.               


276
00:22:32,751 --> 00:22:37,721
- YOU WANT ME TO                
  STAY DOWN HERE? ALONE?        
- YOU STILL HAVE 20 MINUTES.    


277
00:22:45,898 --> 00:22:47,898
                COME ON, SYDNEY.


278
00:22:52,071 --> 00:22:57,274
            HI, KYLE.           
            IT'S ME, JAROD.     
            REMEMBER?           


279
00:22:57,343 --> 00:23:01,111
- [ Kyle ]                      
  WE'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO TALK.   
- WHERE ARE YOU FROM?           


280
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:05,515
        - I DON'T KNOW.         
        - ME NEITHER.           


281
00:23:05,584 --> 00:23:09,085
        I ONLY REMEMBER HERE.   


282
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:12,822
        DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?


283
00:23:15,962 --> 00:23:18,362
[ Rewinds ]                     
        DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?


284
00:23:18,431 --> 00:23:22,700
        WHO YOU ARE?            
         WHO YOU ARE?           


285
00:23:22,768 --> 00:23:25,969
<i>[ Miss Parker ] WHAT DID</i>        
<i>YOU FIND?</i>                       
<i>TEN MILLION BITS OF INFORMATION.</i>


286
00:23:26,037 --> 00:23:29,206
<i>A LOT OF IT'S ABOUT KYLE.</i>       
<i>MY MACHINES ARE SORTING IT</i>      
<i>OUT NOW,</i>                        


287
00:23:29,275 --> 00:23:32,542
BUT I DID MANAGE TO             
TRANSFER ONE SIM                
ONTO A D.S.A. FORMAT.           


288
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:37,948
     - WHAT'S ON IT?            
     - IT'S HOT. I'M TIRED.     


289
00:23:38,016 --> 00:23:43,387
    I'VE BEEN IN MEMPHIS        
    FOR THREE DAYS. CAN'T SLEEP.


290
00:23:43,455 --> 00:23:47,457
    THERE'S TOO MANY PEOPLE     
    OUTSIDE THIS MOTEL.         


291
00:23:47,526 --> 00:23:50,527
I'M GETTING READY.              


292
00:23:52,732 --> 00:23:56,066
        I'M GONNA MAKE HISTORY. 


293
00:23:56,135 --> 00:23:59,502
            I'M GONNA CLOSE     
            A BLEEDING WOUND.   


294
00:23:59,571 --> 00:24:02,238
        YOU DON'T THINK         
        DR. KING IS A GOOD MAN. 


295
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:05,275
NO. HE'S DIVIDING OUR COUNTRY.  


296
00:24:05,344 --> 00:24:07,845
WE HAD LAWS, AND WE HAD ORDER.  


297
00:24:07,913 --> 00:24:11,781
KING DOESN'T OBEY,              
AND AMERICANS, THEY'RE AFRAID.  


298
00:24:11,850 --> 00:24:14,351
             [ Young Raines ]   
             MAYBE IT'S YOU     
             WHO'S AFRAID.      


299
00:24:14,419 --> 00:24:19,590
NO. HE'S THE MENACE.            
KENNEDY GAVE IN TO HIM,         
AND HOOVER CAN'T STOP HIM.      


300
00:24:19,658 --> 00:24:23,694
        <i> IT ENDS NOW.</i>           
        <i> HE HAS TO DIE.</i>         


301
00:24:23,763 --> 00:24:26,329
<i>[ Young Raines ]</i>                
<i>NOW WHO ARE YOU</i>                 
<i>TO MAKE THAT JUDGMENT?</i>          


302
00:24:26,398 --> 00:24:29,833
I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES.     


303
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:35,538
    I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES. 


304
00:24:35,607 --> 00:24:38,708
        - MY GOD! HE DID IT.    
        - DID WHAT?             


305
00:24:38,777 --> 00:24:44,547
RAINES. HE ALWAYS WANTED TO     
DO THIS EXPERIMENT WITH         
ONE OF THE PRETENDERS.          


306
00:24:44,616 --> 00:24:48,619
HE THOUGHT THAT IF              
HE COULD FEED HIM ENOUGH        
NEGATIVE REINFORCEMENT,         


307
00:24:48,687 --> 00:24:50,954
<i>HE COULD STRIP THEM</i>             
<i>OF THEIR MORALITY.</i>              


308
00:24:51,023 --> 00:24:56,326
AND HE COULD, UH,               
CREATE A SOCIOPATH.             


309
00:24:56,395 --> 00:25:00,230
    I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES. 


310
00:25:00,299 --> 00:25:02,565
    I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES. 


311
00:25:10,910 --> 00:25:14,077
    YOU'RE ALL SET THERE.       
    WELCOME TO THE BAY STATE.   


312
00:25:19,551 --> 00:25:22,552
<i>[ Alarm Beeping ]</i>               
<i>[ Young Sydney ] YOUR SHIP</i>      
<i>WAS SPYING IN OUR WATERS.</i>       


313
00:25:22,621 --> 00:25:24,688
WE DEMAND YOU SIGN              
THE ADMISSION OF AGGRESSION.    


314
00:25:24,757 --> 00:25:28,025
- WE'D RATHER DIE.              
- WHAT ABOUT YOU, LIEUTENANT?   


315
00:25:29,861 --> 00:25:31,795
        WELL,                   


316
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:38,034
MAYBE JAROD'S RIGHT.            
             [ Young Raines ]   
             DAMN IT! THAT'S IT.


317
00:25:38,103 --> 00:25:42,272
- [ Young Sydney ]              
  WHAT ARE YOU DOING?           
- I NEVER SHOULD'VE ALLOWED IT. 


318
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:46,176
    - WE'RE ABORTING.           
    - DR. RAINES. DR. RAINES.   


319
00:25:50,182 --> 00:25:52,883
A FLYING CROSS.                 
DID THEY GIVE THIS TO YOU?      


320
00:25:52,952 --> 00:25:55,452
            NO. I'VE JUST       
            ALWAYS HAD IT.      


321
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:59,289
- DR. RAINES LET YOU KEEP IT?   
- DR. RAINES IS MY FRIEND.      


322
00:26:03,462 --> 00:26:07,464
IT'S ORIGAMI.                   
I'LL TEACH YOU HOW TO           
MAKE IT SOMETIME.               


323
00:26:07,533 --> 00:26:12,402
    - WHERE DO THEY KEEP YOU?   
    - THEY TAKE ME DOWN         
      AN ELEVATOR.              


324
00:26:12,471 --> 00:26:18,342
        I'M NOT SURE WHERE,     
        BUT THERE'S SOUNDS      
        IN THE CEILING.         


325
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:22,579
FROM THE AIR VENTS.             
I HEAR THOSE SOUNDS TOO.        


326
00:26:22,648 --> 00:26:24,547
WE MUST BE CLOSE TO EACH OTHER. 


327
00:26:26,318 --> 00:26:31,388
    THE SPEAKER THEY USE        
    TO TALK TO US, IS THERE     
    A WIRE LEADING FROM IT?     


328
00:26:31,457 --> 00:26:33,991
                YEAH. WHY?      


329
00:26:34,059 --> 00:26:38,495
    I THINK I KNOW HOW          
    WE CAN TALK...              
    WITHOUT THEM HEARING US.    


330
00:26:48,507 --> 00:26:50,674
            [ Elevator Dings ]  


331
00:27:01,687 --> 00:27:03,620
    [ Elevator Stops ]          


332
00:27:03,689 --> 00:27:05,856
    WHAT DID YOU DO WITH KYLE?  


333
00:27:05,925 --> 00:27:10,393
DON'T COMMIT POLITICAL SUICIDE  
OVER ANCIENT HISTORY.           


334
00:27:10,462 --> 00:27:15,765
YOU IGNORED A TOWER DIRECTIVE   
WHEN YOU KEPT KYLE HERE         
AFTER HIS RELEASE DATE.         


335
00:27:19,438 --> 00:27:21,371
[ Elevator Starts ]             


336
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:24,942
IF I WERE YOU,                  
I'D STOP DWELLING ON THE PAST.  


337
00:27:25,010 --> 00:27:27,777
JAROD IS YOUR ONLY LIFELINE     
IN THIS PLACE,                  


338
00:27:27,846 --> 00:27:30,680
AND THE LONGER HE'S OUT THERE,  


339
00:27:30,749 --> 00:27:33,983
THE WEAKER YOUR INFLUENCE       
ON HIM BECOMES.                 


340
00:27:34,052 --> 00:27:36,553
<i>[ Elevator Dings ]</i>              


341
00:27:39,057 --> 00:27:44,728
ON MY GRAVE, RAINES,            
IF KYLE IS ALIVE,               
I'LL FIND HIM.                  


342
00:27:46,364 --> 00:27:49,032
        THAT SON OF A BITCH     
        COULD BE ANYWHERE.      


343
00:27:49,101 --> 00:27:53,937
ALL RIGHT. HERE'S A PROFILE     
OUR "PSYCHOLOGICAL GENIUSES"    
HAVE PUT OUT ON JOHN DOE.       


344
00:27:54,006 --> 00:27:57,174
        IN A NUTSHELL, IT SAYS  
        HE'S A TIME BOMB        
        WAITING TO DETONATE.    


345
00:27:57,243 --> 00:27:59,209
        WELCOME TO THE PARTY.   


346
00:27:59,278 --> 00:28:03,012
        FROM HERE ON OUT,       
        I'M ORDERING A PAC      
        ON UP TO A 2-1-11.      


347
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:05,915
    A SHOOT TO KILL ORDER?      


348
00:28:05,984 --> 00:28:09,952
SIR, I ADMIT JOHN DOE           
IS UNPREDICTABLE,               
BUT HE'S NEVER KILLED ANYBODY.  


349
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:12,522
    SPOKEN LIKE                 
    A TRUE CLINTON-ERA RECRUIT. 


350
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:16,759
<i>WE'RE TALKING ABOUT</i>             
<i>A HEAD CASE WHO PUT A CIGARETTE</i> 
<i>OUT ON A MAN'S TONGUE.</i>          


351
00:28:16,828 --> 00:28:18,928
THAT SOUND LIKE SOMEBODY        
YOU WANNA TRY AND REASON WITH?  


352
00:28:25,004 --> 00:28:28,005
ABOUT ANOTHER HALF HOUR         
I'LL HAVE THE NEXT SL 27        
SIM READY TO--                  


353
00:28:29,574 --> 00:28:34,244
    SYDNEY? MISS PARKER?        


354
00:28:44,923 --> 00:28:49,259
    [ Man ] HEY, KIDS,          
    IT'S TIME FOR UNCLE BUDDY'S 
    CARTOON EXTRAVAGANZA.       


355
00:28:49,328 --> 00:28:52,996
    GOD I LOVE THIS SHOW.       
        FASTEN YOUR FUNNY BONES 
        AND WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.


356
00:28:56,768 --> 00:28:59,769
<i>[ Reporter ]</i>                    
<i>NOW A NEWS UPDATE FROM</i>          
<i>THE CHANNEL 3 NEWS CENTER...</i>    


357
00:28:59,838 --> 00:29:02,172
        <i> AND OUR ANCHORPERSON</i>   
        <i> WENDY BARRETT.</i>         


358
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:05,075
    <i> [ Barrett ]</i>                
    <i> WHILE THE F.B.I. CONTINUES</i> 
    <i> ITS DOGGED INVESTIGATION...</i>


359
00:29:05,143 --> 00:29:09,479
<i>OF THE RECENT PRISON ESCAPEE</i>    
<i>KNOWN ONLY AS JOHN DOE,</i>         


360
00:29:09,547 --> 00:29:13,049
    <i> AGENCY AUTHORITIES ADMIT</i>   
    <i> THAT THEY ARE RAPIDLY</i>      
    <i> RUNNING OUT OF LEADS...</i>    


361
00:29:13,118 --> 00:29:16,019
    <i> IN THEIR ATTEMPT TO LOCATE</i> 
    <i> AND APPREHEND--</i>            


362
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:19,055
ANGELO! WHAT ARE YOU DOING      
OUT HERE?                       


363
00:29:19,124 --> 00:29:23,826
<i>AGENT KORKOS IS APPEALING TO</i>    
<i>THE PUBLIC FOR ANY INFORMATION</i>  
<i>THAT MAY LEAD TO DOE'S ARREST,</i>  


364
00:29:23,895 --> 00:29:26,562
<i>AND A REWARD IS BEING OFFERED.</i>  


365
00:29:26,631 --> 00:29:29,232
<i>- AS YOU MAY RECALL, DOE IS--</i>   
- WAIT A MINUTE.                


366
00:29:29,301 --> 00:29:31,601
        [ Clicks Tongue ]       


367
00:29:31,670 --> 00:29:34,671
WAIT, WAIT. I DIDN'T KNOW--     
I DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING. WAIT    
A MINUTE. NO, NO. WAIT. WAIT.   


368
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:38,608
<i>- I DIDN'T-- I DIDN'T MEAN--</i>    
-<i> [ Reporter Continues ]</i>        


369
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:53,023
SL 27?                          


370
00:29:53,926 --> 00:29:55,959
<i>SL 27?</i>                          


371
00:30:00,798 --> 00:30:03,466
    <i> - AND JELL-O BRAINS</i>        
     <i>  TOLD YOU THIS?</i>           
     - NOT WITH WORDS,          


372
00:30:03,535 --> 00:30:05,568
        BUT THERE'S NO DOUBT    
        WHAT HE WAS SAYING.     


373
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:08,638
        JOHN DOE IS KYLE.       


374
00:30:14,145 --> 00:30:16,313
<i>[ Joe Bill ]</i>                    
<i>THEY LIVED UP THERE.</i>            


375
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:29,326
                <i> NOT SO CLEAN.</i>  
                <i> I HAVEN'T NEVER</i>
                <i> BEEN UP HERE.</i>  


376
00:30:29,394 --> 00:30:31,394
                    NOT ALLOWED.


377
00:30:33,398 --> 00:30:37,234
SO EVERYTHING'S JUST            
THE WAY IT WAS WHEN THEY LEFT?  


378
00:30:37,302 --> 00:30:40,903
                    THINK SO.   


379
00:31:06,431 --> 00:31:09,266
            <i> MAN MADE ONE FOR ME</i>
            <i> ONE CHRISTMAS.</i>     


380
00:31:10,902 --> 00:31:13,669
                I LIKED IT.     


381
00:31:13,738 --> 00:31:15,739
<i>[ Baby Crying ]</i>                 


382
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:29,585
    - THERE WAS A BABY HERE.    
    - USED TO HEAR IT CRY.      


383
00:31:29,654 --> 00:31:34,157
    NEVER SAW IT.               
    WASN'T ALLOWED UP HERE.     


384
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:43,899
                WHAT IS IT?     
<i>MY COMPOST PILE.</i>                


385
00:31:45,370 --> 00:31:49,205
                EYES WATCHING ME
                FROM UP HERE.   


386
00:31:49,274 --> 00:31:54,110
        LITTLE EYES. STARING.   


387
00:31:55,313 --> 00:31:57,313
            SCARED ME.          


388
00:32:02,820 --> 00:32:08,491
            NEVER SAW THE BABY, 
            BUT THE BABY SAW ME.


389
00:32:46,364 --> 00:32:48,764
"AND UNDER THE HAND OF GOD,     


390
00:32:48,833 --> 00:32:52,668
YE LITTLE CHILDREN              
SHALL NEVER BE LOST."           


391
00:33:06,518 --> 00:33:08,818
I TOLD YOU--                    
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO WAIT.      


392
00:33:08,887 --> 00:33:11,921
BUT, DADDY, PLEASE.             
I CAN'T HOLD IT ANYMORE.        


393
00:33:11,989 --> 00:33:15,392
        I DON'T CARE IF         
        YOU WET YOUR DAMN PANTS.
        NOW SHUT THE HELL UP!   


394
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:17,427
    HEY! YOU SHOULDN'T          
    TREAT CHILDREN LIKE THAT.   


395
00:33:17,496 --> 00:33:19,796
    [ Groaning ]                
    YOU'RE BREAKING IT.         


396
00:33:19,865 --> 00:33:22,566
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>                    


397
00:33:22,634 --> 00:33:25,168
<i>[ Kyle ]</i>                        
<i>HARRIET.</i>                        


398
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:30,473
YOU SHOULD LOVE YOUR CHILDREN.  
ALWAYS.                         


399
00:33:33,045 --> 00:33:35,512
        HEY, THERE, BIG FELLA.  
        [ Grunts ]              


400
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:39,082
            THE BATHROOM IS     
            RIGHT OVER THERE.   


401
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:41,684
<i>HEY, WHERE YOU GOING?</i>           
<i> HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?</i>     
            [ Starts Engine ]   


402
00:33:41,753 --> 00:33:44,954
WHAT KIND OF PLACE IS THIS?     
THAT'S MY CAR.                  


403
00:33:45,023 --> 00:33:47,524
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE        
WHAT'S ON THIS DISK, SYDNEY.    


404
00:33:47,592 --> 00:33:50,593
        SHOW ME. SHOW ME.       
I'M GLAD YOU'RE ALONE.          


405
00:33:50,662 --> 00:33:55,164
            WHY?                
[ Clears Throat ]               
MISS PARKER.                    


406
00:33:55,233 --> 00:33:58,667
    WELL, I'M NOT SCOOBY-DOO.   
    WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, BROOTS? 


407
00:34:00,405 --> 00:34:02,805
MISS PARKER, I KNOW             
YOU DON'T RESPECT ME,           


408
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:07,043
<i>BUT I JUST DON'T THINK</i>          
<i>YOU SHOULD WATCH THIS DISK.</i>     


409
00:34:07,112 --> 00:34:10,179
            [ Scoffs ]          
            PLAY THE DAMN DISK. 


410
00:34:19,524 --> 00:34:21,458
HATE DICTATES REALITY.          


411
00:34:21,526 --> 00:34:24,361
THE SOONER YOU EMBRACE IT       
AND FOCUS IT UPON YOUR ENEMY,   


412
00:34:24,429 --> 00:34:27,430
        THE SOONER TOTAL CONTROL
        WILL BE REALIZED.       


413
00:34:27,499 --> 00:34:30,466
IT'S MORE THAN JUST A WORD.     


414
00:34:30,535 --> 00:34:35,204
    HATE IS A FEELING.          
    I HAVE IT IN HERE.          


415
00:34:37,275 --> 00:34:39,408
            VERY GOOD, KYLE.    


416
00:34:42,414 --> 00:34:47,416
            FEEL IT GROW.       
            LET IT GROW.        


417
00:34:47,485 --> 00:34:51,253
        TOMORROW I'LL TAKE YOU  
        TO THE JERSEY SHORE,    
        TO THE DRAGON HOUSE.    


418
00:34:53,892 --> 00:34:56,025
    YOU LIKE                    
    THE DRAGON HOUSE, DON'T YOU?


419
00:34:58,029 --> 00:35:02,198
    - I FEEL SAFE THERE.        
    - AND YOU ALWAYS WILL.      


420
00:35:17,949 --> 00:35:23,686
HE WAS TEACHING HIM             
TO HATE MY MOTHER.              
TO SHOOT MY MOTHER.             


421
00:35:23,755 --> 00:35:26,388
I'M SORRY, MISS PARKER.         


422
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:29,124
        THIS EXPLAINS ANGELO'S  
        SUDDEN ATTACK ON YOU.   


423
00:35:30,862 --> 00:35:36,265
    HE WAS JUST SIMULATING      
    KYLE'S INTENSE FEELINGS     
    OF HATRED FOR YOUR MOTHER.  


424
00:35:38,269 --> 00:35:40,536
I HAVE TO TELL                  
MY FATHER ABOUT THIS.           


425
00:35:40,605 --> 00:35:42,972
            [ Snaps Fingers ]   
                IF HE DOESN'T   
                ALREADY KNOW.   


426
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,442
THIS IS THE CENTRE.             


427
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:49,912
        WE'RE TALKING ABOUT     
        MY MOTHER'S DEATH.      


428
00:35:49,981 --> 00:35:54,717
    ALL I AM SAYING IS          
    WE MUST BE CAUTIOUS.        
    ALL THREE OF US.            


429
00:35:58,790 --> 00:36:03,660
EVERYTHING WE HAVE LEARNED      
CAN BE TRACED BACK TO           
SL 27.                          


430
00:36:03,728 --> 00:36:07,396
IF ANYONE                       
FIGURES THAT OUT, WELL.         


431
00:36:11,402 --> 00:36:16,706
ONLY YOUR HEART, PARKER,        
CAN MEASURE THE DEGREE TO WHICH 
YOU SHOULD TRUST YOUR FATHER.   


432
00:36:19,043 --> 00:36:21,644
    JUST BE CAREFUL.            


433
00:36:27,351 --> 00:36:32,188
        [ Clears Throat ]       
        I'M SORRY YOU           
        HAD TO SEE THIS.        


434
00:36:37,028 --> 00:36:40,696
    BROOTS, I DO RESPECT YOU.   


435
00:36:46,905 --> 00:36:50,239
I'M VERY PLEASED WITH THAT.     
OH, THANK YOU.                  


436
00:36:50,308 --> 00:36:54,310
[ Continues, Indistinct ]       
<i>[ Bells Tolling ]</i>               


437
00:36:58,216 --> 00:37:00,516
                        HI.     
                <i> [ Boy ]</i>        
                <i> WAIT UP FOR ME.</i>


438
00:37:00,585 --> 00:37:03,419
LET'S GO GIRLS.                 
WE DON'T WANT TO BE             
LATE FOR CLASS.                 


439
00:37:03,488 --> 00:37:05,621
        <i> EVERYBODY STAY IN LINE.</i>


440
00:37:15,267 --> 00:37:16,899
                    [ Gasps ]   


441
00:37:18,970 --> 00:37:21,537
                HELP! HELP!     


442
00:37:24,108 --> 00:37:25,708
            HARRIET!            


443
00:37:55,439 --> 00:37:58,841
"I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES."   


444
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:12,622
IT'S A ROUGH REPORT. YOU SAID   
THAT IF I LEARNED ANYTHING,     
I SHOULD BRING IT TO YOU?       


445
00:38:12,690 --> 00:38:15,191
MMM.                            


446
00:38:15,259 --> 00:38:19,062
    I'M FIGURING KYLE WAS       
    KEPT HERE AT LEAST 10 YEARS 
    AFTER THE SCHEDULED RELEASE.


447
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:21,631
WHERE DID THESE                 
EXPERIMENTS TAKE PLACE?         


448
00:38:21,699 --> 00:38:24,433
                I'M NOT SURE.   


449
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:27,737
    EXACTLY HOW DID YOU         
    LEARN ABOUT RAINES?         


450
00:38:27,806 --> 00:38:31,040
        I'M S.I.S., DADDY.      
        YOU TAUGHT ME WELL.     


451
00:38:31,109 --> 00:38:34,076
    YOU HAVE PROOF              
    TO BACK THIS UP?            


452
00:38:34,145 --> 00:38:37,780
        I'D HOPED THAT          
        IT WOULD BE ENOUGH      
        I WERE YOUR DAUGHTER.   


453
00:38:37,849 --> 00:38:40,482
OF COURSE. BUT I HAVE PEOPLE    
TO ANSWER TO. I NEED TANGIBLES. 


454
00:38:40,551 --> 00:38:42,952
I HAVE A SOURCE.                
CAN WE JUST LEAVE IT AT THAT?   


455
00:38:43,021 --> 00:38:48,224
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN.              
ANOTHER GARDEN PATH             
OBSCURED BY JAROD'S WEEDS.      


456
00:38:48,293 --> 00:38:51,727
        JAROD HAD ABSOLUTELY    
        NOTHING TO DO WITH ME   
        LEARNING ABOUT THIS.    


457
00:38:53,898 --> 00:38:59,168
THIS REPORT SAYS THAT, UM,      
RAINES TAUGHT KYLE THINGS.      


458
00:38:59,236 --> 00:39:04,440
        - WHAT-WHAT THINGS?     
        - TO HATE. TO KILL.     


459
00:39:06,111 --> 00:39:08,410
        KILL? WHO?              


460
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:12,081
            I'M NOT SURE... YET.


461
00:39:15,420 --> 00:39:17,987
        DID YOU KNOW            
        WHAT RAINES WAS DOING?  


462
00:39:18,056 --> 00:39:20,522
WOULD I HAVE ALLOWED HIM        
TO CONTINUE IF I DID?           


463
00:39:25,863 --> 00:39:28,531
THERE WAS A TIME WHEN           
I KNEW EVERYTHING               
THAT WENT ON HERE.              


464
00:39:28,599 --> 00:39:30,999
MAYBE MY TIME HAS PASSED.       


465
00:39:31,068 --> 00:39:36,772
        I'M SORRY, DADDY.       
        LET ME RUN WITH THIS.   


466
00:39:36,841 --> 00:39:41,844
PLEASE. AND I WILL              
BRING YOU BACK THE BEST         
TANGIBLE EVIDENCE THAT THERE IS.


467
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:45,414
        - WHAT?                 
        - KYLE.                 


468
00:39:57,929 --> 00:40:03,132
            CAN YOU HEAR ME?    
            WHERE ARE YOU?      


469
00:40:03,201 --> 00:40:07,870
THREE DOORS DOWN                
FROM THE CORRIDOR.              
WHERE ARE YOU?                  


470
00:40:07,939 --> 00:40:10,339
    FOUR. I'M RIGHT NEXT TO YOU.


471
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:12,708
                <i> [ Clattering ]</i> 


472
00:40:17,215 --> 00:40:22,217
    - DID YOU HEAR THAT?        
    - YES. MAYBE THEY KNOW.     


473
00:40:22,287 --> 00:40:24,219
    DO YOU THINK                
    THEY KNOW WE'RE TALKING?    


474
00:40:26,724 --> 00:40:28,724
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>SOMEONE DOES.</i>                   


475
00:40:36,834 --> 00:40:39,836
        -<i> THIS IS SYDNEY.</i>       
        - TELL ME ABOUT         
          THE DRAGON HOUSE.     


476
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:45,007
        WAS IT SOME KIND OF     
        AD HOC TORTURE CHAMBER? 


477
00:40:45,076 --> 00:40:48,077
            A CENTRE ASYLUM?    
             A SAFE HOUSE?      


478
00:40:48,146 --> 00:40:52,315
- THIS IS ABOUT KYLE, ISN'T IT? 
- KYLE IS OUT THERE.            


479
00:40:52,383 --> 00:40:54,583
            WAS HE SENT TO KILL 
            MY PARENTS?         


480
00:40:54,652 --> 00:40:57,820
MY GOD, JAROD!                  
I DON'T KNOW. I SWEAR IT.       


481
00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:05,895
    [ Exhales ]                 
    I'LL FIND ANSWERS.          


482
00:41:05,964 --> 00:41:09,465
        QUICKLY, SYDNEY. PLEASE.


483
00:41:16,974 --> 00:41:21,476
SYDNEY.                         
        BROOTS, I NEED YOU TO   
        DO SOMETHING FOR ME.    


484
00:41:21,545 --> 00:41:24,380
<i>SURE, WHAT?</i>                     
        HACK INTO               
        MR. RAINES'S COMPUTER.  


485
00:41:51,575 --> 00:41:55,077
        HEY, PETER.             
        THIS IS DR. JAROD.      
        HOW ARE YOUR GUMS?      


486
00:41:55,146 --> 00:41:57,813
    THEY'RE PINK.               
    LISTEN, I WAS WONDERING--   


487
00:42:01,151 --> 00:42:04,653
                I'D BE HAPPY TO 
                DO YOU A FAVOR. 


488
00:42:04,722 --> 00:42:08,557
NEW ENGLAND AIR?                
I'D LIKE TO BOOK A ROUND-TRIP   
SHUTTLE TO BOSTON, PLEASE.      


489
00:42:12,897 --> 00:42:15,898
    <i> ALL RIGHT.</i>                 
    <i> GATHER AROUND, PEOPLE.</i>     
    <i> WE FINALLY GOT SOMETHING.</i>  


490
00:42:15,966 --> 00:42:20,636
    A PHONE TIP. WITNESS SAW    
    JOHN DOE TRY TO PRY OPEN    
    AN A.T.M. MACHINE IN BOSTON.


491
00:42:20,705 --> 00:42:22,938
A TIP FROM WHOM?                
                SOME KID NAMED  
                GOOFINSKI.      


492
00:42:23,007 --> 00:42:25,508
- WE GOT                        
  THE SURVEILLANCE RIGHT HERE.  
<i>- HOW DO YOU KNOW IT'S HIM?</i>     


493
00:42:25,576 --> 00:42:27,676
<i>LOOK. LOOK AT THAT SCAR, NESS.</i>  
<i>THAT'S HIM.</i>                     


494
00:42:30,247 --> 00:42:33,249
ALL RIGHT. FOSTER, CAINE,       
CHARLES. WE'RE GOING TO BOSTON. 


495
00:42:33,317 --> 00:42:35,618
        I'M CHECKING THIS OUT   
        PERSONALLY.             
WHAT ABOUT ME? I WANT IN.       


496
00:42:35,686 --> 00:42:38,186
LAST THING I NEED IS AN AGENT   
WITH A COLD TRIGGER FINGER...   


497
00:42:38,255 --> 00:42:40,823
    WHEN I TELL THIS CRACKPOT   
    TO PUT HIS CIGARETTE OUT.   
<i>OH, COME ON.</i>                    


498
00:42:40,892 --> 00:42:43,525
            END OF DISCUSSION.  
            YOU'RE AN 18-11     
            ON THIS ONE, NESS.  


499
00:42:43,594 --> 00:42:45,761
OH, GREAT. DESK DUTY.           


500
00:42:47,632 --> 00:42:52,969
THE DRAGON HOUSE IS LOCATED IN  
A PLACE CALLED DELPHI SHORES,   
NEW JERSEY.                     


501
00:42:53,037 --> 00:42:56,372
- THANK YOU, SYDNEY.            
- CHANCES ARE RAINES WILL BE... 


502
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:58,907
        ZEROING IN ON           
        THE DRAGON HOUSE TOO.   


503
00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:04,146
AS YOU KNOW, I HAVE NO CHOICE   
BUT TO GIVE MISS PARKER         
THE SAME INFORMATION.           


504
00:43:04,215 --> 00:43:06,682
        GO THERE                
        AND YOU WON'T BE ALONE. 


505
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:10,086
LONELINESS IS SOMETHING         
I LEFT AT THE CENTRE.           


506
00:43:11,556 --> 00:43:16,358
    ONE LAST THING, JAROD.      
    IF YOU FIND KYLE,           


507
00:43:16,427 --> 00:43:20,763
            YOU HAVE TO KNOW    
            HE'S NOT THE PERSON 
            YOU ONCE KNEW.      


508
00:43:20,831 --> 00:43:23,833
    NEITHER AM I.               


509
00:44:21,392 --> 00:44:23,325
                    <i> [ Harriet ]</i>
                    <i> NO.</i>        


510
00:44:39,009 --> 00:44:43,346
TELL ME WHERE THEY ARE.         
                I CAN'T.        


511
00:44:46,183 --> 00:44:51,186
    I HEARD ONCE THAT           
    THE ANTICIPATION OF PAIN... 


512
00:44:51,255 --> 00:44:54,990
        IS FAR MORE EFFECTIVE   
        THAN PAIN ITSELF.       


513
00:44:56,928 --> 00:44:58,861
                    NOW--       


514
00:45:00,064 --> 00:45:03,432
        WE'RE GONNA FIND OUT.   
<i>[ Thud ]</i>                        


515
00:45:20,951 --> 00:45:25,020
        MY NAME IS JAROD.       
        I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.   


516
00:45:30,094 --> 00:45:33,162
    YOU'RE LATE.                
    SHE'S WITH ME.              


517
00:45:33,231 --> 00:45:36,365
I LOVE A CLASS REUNION.         


518
00:45:39,737 --> 00:45:42,838
                    MR. RAINES. 


519
00:45:42,907 --> 00:45:45,874
    I KNEW I NEVER SHOULD'VE    
    LET YOU TWO GET TOGETHER.   


520
00:45:45,943 --> 00:45:49,545
<i>BOYS, LET'S GO.</i>                 


521
00:45:49,614 --> 00:45:52,415
            I'M NOT GOING       
            ANYWHERE WITH YOU.  


522
00:45:52,483 --> 00:45:54,917
        - NEITHER AM I.         
        - [ Gasps ]             


523
00:45:56,755 --> 00:45:58,922
                GET 'EM!        


524
00:46:06,664 --> 00:46:10,934
        KYLE, YOU KNOW ME.      
        I'M JAROD.              


525
00:46:11,002 --> 00:46:15,271
THEY SAID JAROD WAS DEAD.       
NOW I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES. 


526
00:46:15,339 --> 00:46:19,074
        NOT THIS TIME.          


527
00:46:26,484 --> 00:46:28,584
I HIT THE LOTTO!                


528
00:46:30,155 --> 00:46:33,088
<i>[ Harriet ]</i>                     
<i>JAROD, NO!</i>                      


529
00:46:34,759 --> 00:46:36,526
        [ Miss Parker ]         
        JAROD!                  


530
00:46:43,701 --> 00:46:47,136
    - [ Sydney ]                
      WHICH ONE? WHICH ONE?     
    - GET KYLE!                 


531
00:46:57,448 --> 00:46:59,415
        GET IN.                 


532
00:47:02,420 --> 00:47:04,353
[ Engine Starts ]               


533
00:47:23,007 --> 00:47:25,508
<i>YOU COULD'VE GOTTEN</i>             
<i>US BOTH KILLED.</i>                 


534
00:47:25,576 --> 00:47:28,010
WHY DID YOU STOP ME             
FROM SHOOTING HIM?              


535
00:47:28,079 --> 00:47:32,915
        I STOPPED YOU BECAUSE   
        KYLE IS YOUR BROTHER.   


536
00:47:48,265 --> 00:47:52,468
I DON'T REMEMBER MY PARENTS OR  
ANYTHING ABOUT HAVING A BROTHER.


537
00:47:52,537 --> 00:47:56,705
WELL, YOU WERE VERY YOUNG       
WHEN YOU WERE TAKEN.            
WE OFTEN REPRESS, FORGET.       


538
00:47:56,774 --> 00:47:59,442
        HOW DID THEY COME       
        TO BE WITH YOU?         


539
00:47:59,511 --> 00:48:03,179
WELL, MY OWN PARENTS            
WERE KILLED THREE WEEKS         
BEFORE MY 11th BIRTHDAY.        


540
00:48:03,248 --> 00:48:08,251
I GREW UP IN A CONVENT,         
CONTENT TO GIVE MY LIFE         
SERVING THE CHURCH AS A NUN.    


541
00:48:08,319 --> 00:48:11,820
I HAD SAID MY VOWS              
AND WAS CLOISTERED FOR YEARS.   


542
00:48:11,889 --> 00:48:16,592
BUT IT DIDN'T TAKE.             
            WAS MY FAMILY       
            TIED TO THE CONVENT?


543
00:48:16,661 --> 00:48:20,163
NO, NO.                         
THERE WAS ANOTHER GIRL.         
CATHERINE JAMISON.              


544
00:48:20,231 --> 00:48:23,131
WE WERE REAL RABBLE-ROUSERS.    
GAVE THE MOTHER SUPERIOR HELL.  


545
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:26,168
ONE NIGHT WE SNUCK OUT          
AND WERE CROSSING THIS          
FROZEN POND.                    


546
00:48:26,237 --> 00:48:28,738
    I SLIPPED IN.               
     I WAS DROWNING.            


547
00:48:28,806 --> 00:48:32,608
CATHERINE DOVE IN,              
DRAGGED ME OUT AND THEN         
BREATHED LIFE BACK INTO ME.     


548
00:48:32,676 --> 00:48:37,279
SHE NEVER BECAME A NUN,         
BUT THE SPIRIT                  
THAT GLOWED IN HER...           


549
00:48:37,349 --> 00:48:41,016
WAS SOMETHING I'VE BEEN         
UNABLE TO ACHIEVE               
DESPITE YEARS OF PRAYER.        


550
00:48:41,085 --> 00:48:44,286
THEN AFTER SHE LEFT THE CONVENT,
SHE MARRIED A MAN               
BY THE NAME OF--                


551
00:48:44,355 --> 00:48:47,022
                        PARKER. 
        YES.                    


552
00:48:47,091 --> 00:48:48,925
            CATHERINE PARKER.   


553
00:48:48,993 --> 00:48:51,861
DID YOU KNOW HER?               
                HER DAUGHTER.   


554
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:54,496
    WHAT DID SHE                
    HAVE TO DO WITH MY PARENTS? 


555
00:48:54,565 --> 00:48:58,901
WELL, IN 1969,                  
THE YEAR I INHERITED            
THIS FARM,                      


556
00:48:58,970 --> 00:49:02,137
MOTHER SUPERIOR CALLED          
AND SAID CATHERINE              
NEEDED HELP.                    


557
00:49:02,206 --> 00:49:06,542
CATHERINE SHOWED UP             
AND ASKED ME TO SHELTER         
A MAN AND A WOMAN...            


558
00:49:06,611 --> 00:49:10,613
WHO HAD HAD                     
THEIR TWO YOUNG SONS ABDUCTED.  


559
00:49:10,682 --> 00:49:12,648
        IS THAT WHEN            
        MY PARENTS CAME HERE?   


560
00:49:12,717 --> 00:49:16,552
I KNEW THEM                     
AS CHARLES AND MARGARET.        


561
00:49:16,621 --> 00:49:20,823
THEY WERE AFRAID.               
THEY'D BEEN SEARCHING FOR YEARS,


562
00:49:20,892 --> 00:49:23,192
    AND THEY WERE ON THE RUN.   


563
00:49:23,261 --> 00:49:25,194
            IT WAS SAFE HERE.   


564
00:49:27,165 --> 00:49:29,898
DID THEY EVER TALK              
OR ASK ABOUT ME OR MY BROTHER?  


565
00:49:29,967 --> 00:49:33,502
            THEY NEVER TALKED.  
            I NEVER ASKED.      


566
00:49:33,570 --> 00:49:36,572
    IT WAS TOO PAINFUL.         
    ESPECIALLY FOR YOUR FATHER. 


567
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:38,974
        <i> IT WAS CLEAR HOW DEEPLY</i>
        <i> HE MISSED HIS SONS.</i>    


568
00:49:39,043 --> 00:49:41,877
<i>DID THEY EVER SAY</i>               
<i>WHO THEY THOUGHT</i>                
<i>MIGHT'VE TAKEN US?</i>              


569
00:49:41,946 --> 00:49:45,448
<i>I THINK YOUR FATHER</i>             
<i>WAS AFRAID IT WOULD</i>             
<i>AFFECT YOUR MOTHER'S HEALTH.</i>    


570
00:49:48,319 --> 00:49:50,819
            [ Crying ]          


571
00:49:53,424 --> 00:49:57,593
    THE BABY.                   
<i>SHE GAVE BIRTH TO</i>               
<i>A LITTLE GIRL A MONTH LATER.</i>    


572
00:50:04,102 --> 00:50:08,103
<i>I HAVE A SISTER.</i>                
            <i> HER NAME IS EMILY.</i> 


573
00:50:08,172 --> 00:50:11,040
        EMILY.                  
        <i> [ Harriet Chuckles ]</i>   


574
00:50:11,109 --> 00:50:14,009
        THERE ARE NO PICTURES.  
        I'M SORRY.              


575
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:19,882
YEARS LATER, I STARTED          
GETTING THREATENING PHONE CALLS 
AND LETTERS FROM KYLE.          


576
00:50:19,951 --> 00:50:22,885
<i>HE MUST'VE FIGURED OUT</i>          
<i>I HAD SOME TIE TO YOUR PARENTS.</i> 


577
00:50:22,954 --> 00:50:26,789
HE WAS DESPERATE.               
 HE THOUGHT I COULD HELP HIM.   


578
00:50:28,292 --> 00:50:32,427
IT WAS AFTER THE KIDNAPPING     
THAT YOUR FAMILY VANISHED.      


579
00:50:34,098 --> 00:50:37,099
    YOU'VE BEEN HIDING HERE     
    EVER SINCE.                 


580
00:50:37,168 --> 00:50:40,335
        I'D LOST CONTACT        
        WITH CATHERINE PARKER   
        YEARS EARLIER.          


581
00:50:40,404 --> 00:50:44,773
    I FELT ALONE,               
    AND I WAS AFRAID.           
    SO I WENT UNDERGROUND.      


582
00:50:44,842 --> 00:50:48,277
            <i> YOUR PARENTS</i>       
            <i> LOVED YOU, JAROD.</i>  


583
00:50:48,346 --> 00:50:51,214
    THEY LOVED AND THEY MISSED  
    YOU AND YOUR BROTHER.       


584
00:51:12,570 --> 00:51:17,073
DO YOU REMEMBER                 
WHERE YOU FIRST LIVED           
WHEN YOU CAME TO THE CENTRE?    


585
00:51:19,577 --> 00:51:24,280
    AT FIRST, THREE DOORS DOWN  
    FROM THE CORRIDOR ENTRANCE. 


586
00:51:24,348 --> 00:51:29,518
            LATER, SUBLEVEL--   
WHAT WAS                        
THE MANCHESTER SOLUTION?        


587
00:51:31,355 --> 00:51:33,389
        THE MANCHESTER SOLUTION.


588
00:51:33,458 --> 00:51:39,128
            I-I DON'T REMEMBER  
            ANY SOLUTION BECAUSE
            THE JOB WAS BLOWN.  


589
00:51:39,197 --> 00:51:42,198
    I COULD'VE DONE IT ALONE.   
     I SIMMED IT CORRECT--      
        [ Whirring ]            


590
00:51:45,869 --> 00:51:49,037
    THE OTHERS LOST THE WILL,   
    BUT I DIDN'T.               


591
00:51:49,107 --> 00:51:52,374
    I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES. 
     I DECIDE WHO LIVES OR DIES.


592
00:51:52,443 --> 00:51:55,945
                    [ Whirring ]


593
00:51:56,013 --> 00:51:59,681
    YOU SAID AFTER              
    ALL THOSE YEARS IN PRISON,  
    HE'D REMEMBER NOTHING.      


594
00:51:59,750 --> 00:52:02,919
HE CAN'T                        
REMEMBER EVERYTHING.            
        HE REMEMBERS TOO MUCH.  


595
00:52:02,987 --> 00:52:05,020
    JAROD ALONE IS BAD ENOUGH.  


596
00:52:05,089 --> 00:52:08,757
I BROUGHT HIM IN.               
WHY IS<i> HE</i> HERE?                 


597
00:52:08,826 --> 00:52:13,162
            I ASKED HIM TO BE.  
WHO IN THE HELL                 
IS KYLE ANYWAY?                 


598
00:52:13,231 --> 00:52:15,564
OR SHOULD I SAY<i> WHAT?</i>           


599
00:52:15,633 --> 00:52:17,966
            KYLE IS SOMEONE     
            OF CONCERN TO ME.   


600
00:52:18,035 --> 00:52:22,504
    YOU MISSED JAROD.           
    IT WAS YOUR BEST CHANCE,    
    AND HE'S STILL OUT THERE.   


601
00:52:22,573 --> 00:52:25,240
            I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET.


602
00:52:25,309 --> 00:52:28,710
        I SHOULD'VE TOLD YOU    
        THAT I HAD BROUGHT      
        MR. RAINES IN ON THIS.  


603
00:52:28,779 --> 00:52:32,247
                I APOLOGIZE.    
                BUT THINGS WERE 
                MOVING QUICKLY. 


604
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:34,983
            NOW MR. RAINES AND I
            WILL HANDLE KYLE.   


605
00:52:35,052 --> 00:52:38,187
BUT, DADDY--                    
                NO, NO, NO.     
                TRUST ME.       


606
00:52:39,556 --> 00:52:44,726
SYDNEY, DO YOU THINK            
JAROD MIGHT RETURN              
TO THE CENTRE?                  


607
00:52:44,795 --> 00:52:47,997
            THERE'S NOTHING HERE
            THAT JAROD WANTS.   


608
00:52:48,065 --> 00:52:50,566
    AND JAROD ALWAYS HAS        
    AN OBJECTIVE.               


609
00:52:50,634 --> 00:52:53,034
    BESIDES, EVEN THOUGH        
    WE NEVER FIGURED OUT        
    HOW HE GOT OUT,             


610
00:52:53,103 --> 00:52:58,207
OUR LATEST SECURITY             
IMPROVEMENTS ARE QUITE BEYOND   
ANYONE'S CAPABILITIES.          


611
00:52:58,276 --> 00:53:00,709
        EVEN JAROD'S.           


612
00:53:07,885 --> 00:53:11,720
THAT'S THE FIRST TIME           
I HAVE EVER HEARD YOU           
DOUBT JAROD'S ABILITIES.        


613
00:53:11,788 --> 00:53:15,957
            LET'S JUST HOPE     
            THEY BELIEVED IT    
            AS MUCH AS YOU DID. 


614
00:53:36,280 --> 00:53:39,948
    - GET HIM OUT OF HERE.      
    - NO! JAROD, HELP!          


615
00:53:40,017 --> 00:53:42,984
NO, LEAVE ME ALONE.             


616
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:46,755
JAROD! JAROD!                   


617
00:53:46,824 --> 00:53:49,224
                <i> JAROD, HELP ME!</i>


618
00:54:39,644 --> 00:54:42,144
<i>[ Dog Barking In Distance ]</i>     


619
00:54:44,649 --> 00:54:47,449
YOU SAID IT WAS                 
A MATTER OF GREAT IMPORTANCE.   


620
00:54:47,518 --> 00:54:50,519
[ Quietly ]                     
I WANT YOU TO HELP ME           
GET TO KYLE.                    


621
00:54:50,587 --> 00:54:55,090
WHY?                            
    BECAUSE HE KNOWS SOMETHING  
    ABOUT MY MOTHER'S DEATH.    


622
00:55:01,265 --> 00:55:03,531
    WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO?  
    BEG?                        


623
00:55:03,600 --> 00:55:05,534
        <i> [ Birds Fluttering ]</i>   


624
00:55:09,873 --> 00:55:12,541
WHAT MAKES YOU SO CERTAIN       
THAT KYLE CAN HELP YOU?         


625
00:55:12,610 --> 00:55:14,976
    BECAUSE HE WAS              
    MR. RAINES'S PET PROJECT.   


626
00:55:17,148 --> 00:55:21,816
I FEEL IT. SYDNEY, I FEEL IT.   
KYLE KNOWS WHO KILLED MY MOTHER.


627
00:55:25,289 --> 00:55:28,790
LOOK, THEY'RE                   
KEEPING HIM IN A SECTION        
I DON'T HAVE ACCESS TO.         


628
00:55:28,859 --> 00:55:32,661
ALSO, THEY'RE MONITORING HIM    
ROUND THE CLOCK                 
FROM THE TECH ROOM.             


629
00:55:32,730 --> 00:55:37,233
THERE'S JUST NO WAY FOR         
ANYONE TO GET THERE UNDETECTED. 


630
00:55:37,301 --> 00:55:42,971
        RIGHT?                  
        MMM, WELL, THAT'S NOT   
        ENTIRELY TRUE.          


631
00:55:44,909 --> 00:55:48,076
        WHAT DO YOU MEAN?       


632
00:55:48,145 --> 00:55:51,146
        I MEAN, I GOT US INTO   
        SL 27, DIDN'T I?        


633
00:55:52,883 --> 00:55:56,551
        I COULD PROBABLY        
        BYPASS THE SENSORS...   


634
00:55:56,620 --> 00:56:01,623
    AND AT A DESIGNATED TIME,   
    LOOP THE CAMERA FEED        
    INTO THE MONITOR SYSTEM.    


635
00:56:01,691 --> 00:56:03,858
WELL, FOR HOW LONG?             


636
00:56:05,262 --> 00:56:07,429
            MMM, LONG ENOUGH.   


637
00:56:13,637 --> 00:56:15,971
        [ Chattering ]          


638
00:56:42,500 --> 00:56:47,769
I WAS LOOKING FOR--             
HERE.                           


639
00:56:47,838 --> 00:56:49,171
                    [ Beeps ]   


640
00:57:00,517 --> 00:57:03,085
        [ Groans ]              
        OH, THAT'S HOT!         


641
00:57:03,153 --> 00:57:07,622
<i>THAT-- [ Grunts ]</i>               
<i>I'M SORRY. IT'S OKAY. GOT IT.</i>   


642
00:57:20,304 --> 00:57:22,203
YOU LOOK JUST LIKE HER.         


643
00:57:23,274 --> 00:57:25,507
    THAT'S WHAT THEY TELL ME.   


644
00:57:49,700 --> 00:57:54,036
    YOU'RE THE ONE WHO DECIDES  
    WHO LIVES OR DIES, RIGHT?   


645
00:57:56,540 --> 00:58:00,308
    - YOU KNOW MY WORK.         
    - DID YOU KILL MY MOTHER?   


646
00:58:10,487 --> 00:58:14,323
        DID YOU KILL MY MOTHER? 


647
00:58:18,295 --> 00:58:22,063
NO.                             
            THEN WHO?           


648
00:58:29,739 --> 00:58:32,707
            WAS IT MR. RAINES?  


649
00:58:40,851 --> 00:58:43,184
             [ Elevator Buzzes ]


650
00:58:47,691 --> 00:58:50,191
        WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?


651
00:58:50,260 --> 00:58:54,429
I WAS TRYING TO FIND            
MY WAY TO THE, UH,              
NEW ACCOUNTING OFFICES.         


652
00:58:56,933 --> 00:59:00,435
                WHY DO I THINK  
                YOU'RE LYING?   


653
00:59:00,504 --> 00:59:03,004
                OPEN THE DOOR.  


654
00:59:05,809 --> 00:59:08,043
<i>[ Wheels Squeaking ]</i>            


655
00:59:09,046 --> 00:59:10,579
<i>[ Metal Rattles ]</i>               


656
00:59:27,831 --> 00:59:29,764
            GET HIM OUT OF HERE.


657
00:59:48,853 --> 00:59:52,020
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>MY PARENTS MUST HAVE</i>            
<i>LOVED THIS PLACE.</i>               


658
00:59:58,295 --> 01:00:00,262
I MAY KNOW SOMEONE...           


659
01:00:00,331 --> 01:00:02,530
WHO CAN HELP YOU FIND           
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.        


660
01:00:02,599 --> 01:00:05,200
                    WHO?        


661
01:00:05,269 --> 01:00:08,370
[ Chuckles ]                    
SOLEMN VOWS DIE HARD.           


662
01:00:10,407 --> 01:00:12,374
    I'LL HAVE TO GO             
    AND SEE THEM.               


663
01:00:12,442 --> 01:00:14,376
        ALONE.                  


664
01:00:15,446 --> 01:00:17,378
            IT'S TOO DANGEROUS. 


665
01:00:17,447 --> 01:00:22,517
CATHERINE DIDN'T THINK          
OF HERSELF WHEN SHE PULLED ME   
OUT OF THAT ICY POND.           


666
01:00:24,488 --> 01:00:26,421
[ Sighs ]                       


667
01:00:26,490 --> 01:00:29,658
I'LL BE--                       
 I'LL BE GONE A FEW DAYS.       


668
01:00:31,428 --> 01:00:34,229
            I WON'T BE HERE.    


669
01:00:39,403 --> 01:00:42,470
        I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT 
        SINCE I BROKE OUT...    


670
01:00:42,540 --> 01:00:47,342
        SEARCHING AND HUNTING   
        FOR SOME CLUE THAT MIGHT
        LEAD ME TO MY PAST.     


671
01:00:48,913 --> 01:00:52,047
        AND RIGHT NOW,          
        THE BIGGEST CLUE TO IT  
        IS BACK WHERE I STARTED.


672
01:00:53,350 --> 01:00:55,416
    I DON'T UNDERSTAND.         


673
01:00:56,854 --> 01:00:58,854
    I'M GOING TO GET MY BROTHER.


674
01:01:00,090 --> 01:01:02,023
        I'M GOING BACK          
        TO THE CENTRE.          


675
01:01:37,961 --> 01:01:39,894
        HELLO, SYDNEY.          


676
01:01:39,963 --> 01:01:42,630
                MY GOD.         


677
01:01:42,699 --> 01:01:44,766
        HOW'D YOU GET IN?       


678
01:01:46,804 --> 01:01:49,471
THE SAME WAY I GOT OUT.         


679
01:01:49,540 --> 01:01:53,541
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME          
ABOUT MY FAMILY?                
ABOUT MY BROTHER?               


680
01:01:53,610 --> 01:01:56,878
        - YOUR BROTHER?         
        - KYLE.                 


681
01:01:56,947 --> 01:01:59,548
    AT LEAST THAT'S WHAT        
    I THINK HIS NAME IS.        


682
01:01:59,616 --> 01:02:02,951
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?         
                I DIDN'T KNOW.  


683
01:02:04,187 --> 01:02:06,120
    <i> ALL I KNOW ABOUT KYLE IS--</i> 


684
01:02:09,426 --> 01:02:12,660
            ACTUALLY,           
            WHAT JACOB TOLD ME. 


685
01:02:14,898 --> 01:02:17,399
        <i> [ Wheels Squeaking ]</i>   


686
01:02:26,610 --> 01:02:28,610
AM I INTERRUPTING SOMETHING?    


687
01:02:28,678 --> 01:02:31,279
        OH. JUST GOING OVER     
        SOME NOTES.             


688
01:02:31,347 --> 01:02:33,281
OF COURSE.                      


689
01:02:33,350 --> 01:02:35,983
ALWAYS THE CONSCIENTIOUS ONE.   


690
01:02:36,052 --> 01:02:40,855
YOU WILL NOTIFY ME              
IF JAROD ATTEMPTS               
TO MAKE CONTACT WITH YOU.       


691
01:02:40,924 --> 01:02:42,824
            WHAT IF HE CONTACTS 
            YOU FIRST?          


692
01:02:56,507 --> 01:02:58,439
                [ Whispers ]    
                JAROD.          


693
01:02:58,509 --> 01:03:00,441
                JAROD.          


694
01:03:19,930 --> 01:03:22,297
            JAROD, HELP ME!     


695
01:04:06,476 --> 01:04:08,710
<i>[ Clinking ]</i>                    


696
01:04:20,590 --> 01:04:21,923
                ANGELO.         


697
01:04:25,495 --> 01:04:27,728
                ANGELO.         


698
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:32,100
                    [ Laughs ]  


699
01:04:33,836 --> 01:04:35,770
            LOOK AT YOUR HAIR.  
<i>[ Soft Thud ]</i>                   


700
01:04:41,311 --> 01:04:43,244
            CRACKER JACK.       


701
01:04:44,647 --> 01:04:47,215
                        C.J.    


702
01:04:47,284 --> 01:04:48,916
                YOU'RE C.J.     


703
01:04:48,985 --> 01:04:52,119
        YOU WROTE THOSE LETTERS 
        TO KYLE IN PRISON.      


704
01:04:52,188 --> 01:04:55,656
    YOU'VE BEEN IN CONTACT      
    WITH HIM JUST LIKE YOU'VE   
    BEEN IN CONTACT WITH ME.    


705
01:05:02,699 --> 01:05:04,866
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME           
SINCE WE'VE HAD TO PERFORM...   


706
01:05:04,935 --> 01:05:07,803
THIS KIND OF A RADICAL          
PROCEDURE, DR. RAINES.          


707
01:05:07,871 --> 01:05:11,039
    AND THE TOWER HASN'T MADE   
    THEIR APPROVAL CLEAR YET.   


708
01:05:11,108 --> 01:05:13,208
I'VE MADE THE DIAGNOSIS.        


709
01:05:13,277 --> 01:05:17,612
A FRONTAL LOBE SEPARATION       
IS THE ONLY WAY                 
TO BRING HIM PEACE.             


710
01:05:17,681 --> 01:05:20,282
UNLESS YOU'D LIKE TO OFFER      
A DIFFERING OPINION.            


711
01:05:20,350 --> 01:05:23,351
                    [ Rattles ] 
    I'LL CALL FOR ANESTHESIA.   


712
01:05:23,420 --> 01:05:25,786
            HE'LL BE READY      
            IN 10 MINUTES.      


713
01:05:25,855 --> 01:05:28,089
            RAINES.             


714
01:05:33,096 --> 01:05:36,263
                RAINES!         


715
01:05:52,783 --> 01:05:54,782
        WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?   


716
01:05:54,851 --> 01:05:57,118
            I'M JAROD.          


717
01:06:04,728 --> 01:06:06,661
    RAINES SAID YOU WERE DEAD.  


718
01:06:06,730 --> 01:06:09,097
            NOT HARDLY.         


719
01:06:09,165 --> 01:06:11,099
        WHY ARE YOU HELPING ME? 


720
01:06:11,167 --> 01:06:14,235
    BECAUSE...                  
    I'M YOUR BROTHER.           


721
01:06:16,439 --> 01:06:19,441
    - I DON'T HAVE ANY FAMILY.  
    - YES. YOU DO.              


722
01:06:20,777 --> 01:06:24,979
I'M GUESSING...                 
OUR FATHER GAVE YOU THIS.       


723
01:06:29,786 --> 01:06:32,019
            MY GOD.             


724
01:06:32,088 --> 01:06:35,090
        - YOU KEPT IT.          
        - NOT ME.               


725
01:06:35,158 --> 01:06:37,158
                        HE DID. 


726
01:06:40,330 --> 01:06:42,563
<i>COME ON.</i>                        
<i>IT'S TIME WE ALL WERE FREE.</i>     


727
01:06:46,136 --> 01:06:48,569
                [ Yelling ]     


728
01:06:51,774 --> 01:06:54,842
        -<i> [ Kyle Yelling ]</i>      
        -<i> NO! NO! NO!</i>           


729
01:06:55,845 --> 01:06:57,945
            NOBODY GETS HURT.   


730
01:06:58,014 --> 01:06:59,947
    WHERE ARE WE GOING?         


731
01:07:00,016 --> 01:07:02,016
                        HOME.   


732
01:07:03,286 --> 01:07:05,220
                ANGELO, COME ON.
                GET IN.         


733
01:07:07,491 --> 01:07:09,491
            NO.                 


734
01:07:09,559 --> 01:07:12,393
    I DECIDE WHO LIVES          
    OR DIES.                    


735
01:07:12,462 --> 01:07:15,062
        -<i> [ Alarm Blaring ]</i>     
        - ANGELO. ANGELO, NO!   


736
01:07:21,671 --> 01:07:23,871
<i>[ Alarm Blaring ]</i>               


737
01:07:25,675 --> 01:07:27,642
        HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?    


738
01:07:27,711 --> 01:07:30,110
    ALARM SENSORS INDICATE      
    THEY'RE IN SL 19.           


739
01:07:30,179 --> 01:07:32,146
    I'M ON IT.                  


740
01:07:35,318 --> 01:07:37,384
            I NEED TO SPEAK TO  
            MR. PARKER.         


741
01:07:39,656 --> 01:07:41,589
THIS WAY.                       
            WHERE DOES IT LEAD? 


742
01:07:41,658 --> 01:07:44,058
    OUT. COME ON.               


743
01:07:44,127 --> 01:07:46,461
                    WE'RE ON 19.


744
01:07:46,530 --> 01:07:49,064
        BROOTS, WHERE ARE THEY? 


745
01:07:49,132 --> 01:07:50,932
    I'M WORKING ON IT.          
     I'M WORKING ON IT.         


746
01:07:51,000 --> 01:07:52,901
                GO DOWN TO 20.  
    [ Grumbles ]                


747
01:08:00,210 --> 01:08:02,777
    MISS PARKER,                
    I'M GETTING A SIGNAL        
    IN THE MOTION DETECTORS.    


748
01:08:02,846 --> 01:08:05,646
        THEY'RE IN              
        THE VENTILATION SYSTEM. 
        RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.    


749
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:09,683
            RIP THAT DOWN.      


750
01:08:13,223 --> 01:08:16,091
            DAMN IT.            
            IT'S COUSIN ITT.    


751
01:08:18,495 --> 01:08:20,028
        IT'S ANGELO.            


752
01:08:26,636 --> 01:08:28,570
        [ Grunts ]              


753
01:08:45,088 --> 01:08:46,220
            COME ON.            


754
01:08:48,758 --> 01:08:51,492
        TRUST ME.               


755
01:08:58,100 --> 01:09:00,034
TELL ME THIS WASN'T             
YOU, DADDY.                     


756
01:09:00,102 --> 01:09:02,503
I KNOW BETTER.                  


757
01:09:02,572 --> 01:09:05,640
I DID NOT AUTHORIZE             
THIS PROCEDURE.                 


758
01:09:06,910 --> 01:09:08,843
I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.          


759
01:09:10,146 --> 01:09:13,648
RAINES WAS PREPARED TO DESTROY  
A CENTRE INVESTMENT...          


760
01:09:13,716 --> 01:09:15,683
WITH NO DIRECTIVE               
FROM THE TOWER...               


761
01:09:15,752 --> 01:09:18,986
TO PROTECT HIMSELF              
FROM WHAT KYLE KNOWS.           


762
01:09:20,122 --> 01:09:22,690
WE'VE BOTH BEEN FEELING IT      
FOR A LONG TIME.                


763
01:09:25,227 --> 01:09:27,462
        RAINES HAS HAD HIS OWN  
        AGENDA LONG ENOUGH.     


764
01:09:27,530 --> 01:09:29,464
HE'LL BE DEALT WITH.            


765
01:09:29,532 --> 01:09:32,834
JUST BRING ME BACK              
WHAT BELONGS TO THE CENTRE.     


766
01:09:48,517 --> 01:09:51,686
        [ Yells ]               


767
01:09:51,754 --> 01:09:53,621
                    IT'S OKAY.  
[ Yells ]                       


768
01:09:53,689 --> 01:09:56,457
                    IT'S OKAY.  
                     IT'S OKAY. 


769
01:09:56,526 --> 01:09:58,559
                        HERE.   


770
01:09:58,627 --> 01:10:01,061
                IT'S ONE OF     
                THE SMALL JOYS  
                OF FREEDOM.     


771
01:10:01,130 --> 01:10:03,564
            THERE'S CANDY       
            UNDERNEATH THE HEAD.


772
01:10:10,273 --> 01:10:12,307
                    AH--        


773
01:10:12,375 --> 01:10:15,142
            <i> THAT'S OKAY.</i>       
            <i> I HAVE PLENTY MORE.</i>


774
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:23,150
        WE JUST GONNA DRIVE?    


775
01:10:24,221 --> 01:10:26,220
        I KNOW A PLACE          
        WHERE WE CAN REST.      


776
01:10:30,894 --> 01:10:32,827
HOW LONG YOU BEEN OUT?          


777
01:10:35,098 --> 01:10:37,064
            ALMOST A YEAR NOW.  


778
01:10:38,534 --> 01:10:41,101
<i>THERE'S SO MUCH OUT HERE.</i>       


779
01:10:41,170 --> 01:10:44,338
    YOU HAVE SO MUCH            
    CATCHING UP TO DO.          


780
01:10:50,212 --> 01:10:52,747
    YOU DO REMEMBER.            


781
01:11:01,991 --> 01:11:05,359
    THAT KYLE WAS               
    A MILLION YEARS AGO, JAROD. 


782
01:11:05,428 --> 01:11:08,529
        <i> BY THE TIME I BROKE</i>    
        <i> FROM THE CENTRE,</i>       
        <i> MY HEAD WAS MUSH.</i>      


783
01:11:10,699 --> 01:11:14,134
        ALL I THOUGHT ABOUT     
        WAS FINDING MY--        


784
01:11:14,204 --> 01:11:16,136
        FINDING OUR PARENTS.    


785
01:11:16,205 --> 01:11:19,207
<i>AND ANYBODY GOT IN MY WAY,</i>      
<i>I JUST RAN OVER 'EM.</i>            


786
01:11:19,275 --> 01:11:23,278
    BEFORE LONG,                
    I WAS RUNNING FROM THE LAW. 


787
01:11:24,781 --> 01:11:27,448
        BY THE TIME             
        I FIGURED THINGS OUT    
        AND GOT TO HARRIET,     


788
01:11:28,518 --> 01:11:30,618
<i>I JUST--</i>                        


789
01:11:30,687 --> 01:11:33,288
    I NEVER WANTED TO HURT HER. 


790
01:11:38,861 --> 01:11:41,029
    I JUST THOUGHT              
    SHE KNEW WHERE THEY WERE.   


791
01:11:46,703 --> 01:11:49,637
                [ Jarod ]       
                SOMETHING GOOD  
                CAME OUT OF IT. 


792
01:11:49,705 --> 01:11:52,640
            AT LEAST WE HAVE    
            A PLACE TO START.   


793
01:12:01,785 --> 01:12:03,717
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>WELL, THAT'S THE REST OF IT.</i>    


794
01:12:03,786 --> 01:12:05,719
        HE'S GONE THROUGH       
        EVERYTHING WE HAVE.     


795
01:12:05,789 --> 01:12:08,355
    JAROD'S NOTEBOOKS,          
    F.B.I. FILES, EVERYTHING    
    WE'VE GOT ON KYLE.          


796
01:12:08,424 --> 01:12:10,792
HE'S ALMOST DONE.               


797
01:12:10,860 --> 01:12:13,060
        [ Sydney ]              
        REAL GLUTTON            
        FOR PUNISHMENT, HMM?    


798
01:12:13,129 --> 01:12:15,997
    DESPERATE TIMES,            
     DESPERATE MEASURES, SYDNEY.


799
01:12:16,065 --> 01:12:20,734
IF SPONGE BOY HERE REALLY CAN   
BECOME ANYONE, LIKE ALL         
THE QUACKS AROUND HERE CLAIM,   


800
01:12:20,803 --> 01:12:24,171
    THEN I'M LETTING HIM        
    BECOME KYLE AND JAROD       
    AT THE SAME TIME.           


801
01:12:24,240 --> 01:12:27,008
    MAYBE HE'LL TELL ME         
    WHERE THEY WENT.            
                    [ Yells ]   


802
01:12:29,345 --> 01:12:31,245
MAYBE WE SHOULD HAVE            
TETHERED HIM.                   


803
01:12:31,314 --> 01:12:35,216
        AREN'T WE MAKING ONE    
        ERRONEOUS ASSUMPTION,   
        DR. PARKER?             


804
01:12:35,285 --> 01:12:37,218
WHAT'S HE GONNA BLOW?           
A TRANSISTOR?                   


805
01:12:37,287 --> 01:12:41,589
        YOU ASSUME THAT         
        HE WANTS TO HELP YOU.   
    WHY WOULDN'T HE?            


806
01:12:41,658 --> 01:12:45,126
            JUST LET THIS QUACK 
            HANDLE IT, HMM?     


807
01:12:50,000 --> 01:12:52,000
JAROD.                          


808
01:12:54,638 --> 01:12:58,239
JAROD. IF YOU'RE REALLY         
IN THERE, JAROD,                


809
01:12:58,307 --> 01:13:00,241
THEN YOU'LL KNOW WHO I AM...    


810
01:13:00,310 --> 01:13:02,276
    AND THAT I CAN HELP YOU.    


811
01:13:02,345 --> 01:13:05,913
        ALSO, THAT I AM         
        THE ONLY ONE...         


812
01:13:05,981 --> 01:13:08,916
        WHO CAN PROTECT YOU     
        FROM MR. RAINES.        


813
01:13:18,127 --> 01:13:20,261
            [ Grunting ]        


814
01:13:21,130 --> 01:13:22,730
    EASY. EASY.                 


815
01:13:34,310 --> 01:13:36,543
        I'M GOING HOME.         


816
01:13:36,612 --> 01:13:39,346
        I'M SAFE HERE.          


817
01:13:42,985 --> 01:13:46,020
KYLE KIDNAPPED A WOMAN          
NAMED HARRIET TASHMAN.          


818
01:13:46,088 --> 01:13:48,489
HE WAS TRYING TO GET HER        
TO THIS PLACE.                  


819
01:13:53,196 --> 01:13:55,262
[ Wheels Squeaking ]            


820
01:13:58,100 --> 01:14:02,269
        I CAN FEEL THEM HERE.   
    I KNOW.                     


821
01:14:02,339 --> 01:14:04,706
                BUT THEY DON'T  
                HAVE FACES.     


822
01:14:04,774 --> 01:14:07,608
'CAUSE WE DON'T REMEMBER.       


823
01:14:07,677 --> 01:14:10,010
OR THE CENTRE                   
DIDN'T LET US REMEMBER.         


824
01:14:12,482 --> 01:14:14,482
        MAYBE THIS WILL HELP.   


825
01:14:20,223 --> 01:14:22,223
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.                


826
01:14:24,761 --> 01:14:27,061
THEY'RE STILL OUT THERE,        
AREN'T THEY?                    


827
01:14:27,129 --> 01:14:29,864
                    YES. THEM...


828
01:14:29,932 --> 01:14:31,932
                AND OUR SISTER. 


829
01:14:34,036 --> 01:14:36,404
            SHE WAS BORN        
            AFTER WE WERE GONE. 


830
01:14:50,687 --> 01:14:52,687
                DAD TAUGHT ME.  


831
01:14:55,725 --> 01:14:57,759
    WE'RE GOING TO FIND THEM.   


832
01:14:57,827 --> 01:15:00,995
        WE WOULDN'T HAVE        
        GOTTEN THIS FAR UNLESS  
        WE WERE MEANT TO.       


833
01:15:03,266 --> 01:15:05,332
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>


834
01:15:05,401 --> 01:15:07,602
            KORKOS.             


835
01:15:07,670 --> 01:15:11,272
            DO YOU WANT TO KNOW 
            WHERE JOHN DOE IS?  


836
01:15:20,149 --> 01:15:22,149
<i>[ Metal Clangs ]</i>                


837
01:15:32,328 --> 01:15:34,595
            <i> HARRIET.</i>           


838
01:15:34,664 --> 01:15:36,697
    WE DIDN'T KNOW IT WAS YOU.  


839
01:15:39,268 --> 01:15:41,268
    IT'S ALL RIGHT.             


840
01:15:45,275 --> 01:15:47,375
        I HAVE SOME GOOD NEWS.  
<i>[ Vehicle Approaching ]</i>         


841
01:15:47,444 --> 01:15:49,410
SOMEBODY'S COMING UP THE ROAD.  


842
01:15:52,482 --> 01:15:54,415
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.          


843
01:16:28,184 --> 01:16:30,585
                GET 'EM.        


844
01:16:41,164 --> 01:16:43,097
            [ Jarod ]           
            HOLD ON!            


845
01:16:50,706 --> 01:16:52,673
            [ Yells ]           


846
01:16:52,742 --> 01:16:55,510
        - [ Groans ]            
        - KYLE.                 


847
01:16:55,579 --> 01:16:57,545
    - KYLE!                     
    - HOLD STILL. LET ME LOOK.  


848
01:16:57,613 --> 01:17:00,681
            NO. GO.             
            MY LEG IS BROKEN.   


849
01:17:00,750 --> 01:17:02,516
            NO. I'M NOT GOING TO
            LEAVE YOU HERE.     


850
01:17:02,585 --> 01:17:04,952
            JAROD, GO!          
            FIND OUR PARENTS.   


851
01:17:13,597 --> 01:17:15,562
DON'T TELL THEM WHAT I BECAME.  


852
01:17:15,631 --> 01:17:18,032
                <i> COME ON, JAROD.</i>


853
01:17:22,038 --> 01:17:26,206
                <i> COME ON, JAROD.</i>
                 <i> COME ON.</i>      


854
01:17:30,814 --> 01:17:33,214
            FREEZE. F.B.I.      


855
01:17:48,765 --> 01:17:52,600
                    NO!         


856
01:18:05,481 --> 01:18:08,549
COME ON, JAROD. JAROD.          


857
01:18:08,617 --> 01:18:10,284
                JAROD.          


858
01:18:13,957 --> 01:18:15,890
                        JAROD.  


859
01:18:15,959 --> 01:18:18,592
    JAROD, WE HAVE TO SPLIT UP. 
NO. COME ON.                    
I CAN PROTECT YOU.              


860
01:18:18,661 --> 01:18:20,828
                NO. THIS IS NOT 
                ABOUT ME NOW.   


861
01:18:20,897 --> 01:18:23,130
            YOUR PARENTS.       
            THEY'RE IN BOSTON.  


862
01:18:23,199 --> 01:18:25,566
        THEY'LL ARRIVE BY TAXI  
        AT THIS COFFEE SHOP.    


863
01:18:25,635 --> 01:18:28,235
            HERE'S THE ADDRESS  
            AND MEET TIME.      
            TOMORROW AT 3:00.   


864
01:18:28,304 --> 01:18:30,271
HARRIET, THANK YOU.             


865
01:18:46,255 --> 01:18:49,223
        IT WAS A PRUDENT MOVE   
        WITH KYLE.              


866
01:18:49,292 --> 01:18:51,292
        <i> KEEPS OUR HANDS CLEAN.</i> 


867
01:18:51,361 --> 01:18:54,194
<i>[ Mr. Parker ]</i>                  
<i>I THINK WE SHOULD FOCUS ON</i>      
<i>BRINGING JAROD IN.</i>              


868
01:18:54,263 --> 01:18:56,196
    WE HAVE A POSSIBLE LOCATION.


869
01:18:56,265 --> 01:19:00,534
                WHERE? WHEN?    
        3:00. TODAY.            


870
01:19:00,603 --> 01:19:04,505
        <i> TAKE A SWEEPER TEAM</i>    
        <i> WITH YOU.</i>              
        <i> BRING HIM BACK.</i>        


871
01:19:04,574 --> 01:19:06,574
        <i> [ Wheels Squeaking ]</i>   


872
01:19:11,147 --> 01:19:13,480
            <i> [ Bell Tolling ]</i>   


873
01:19:56,192 --> 01:19:58,559
        WE'RE FLYING BLIND.     
                    NO NEED,    
                    MISS PARKER.


874
01:19:58,628 --> 01:20:02,362
WELL, DON'T COUNT ON MR. RAINES 
FEELING THE SAME WAY.           
                    I DON'T.    


875
01:20:02,431 --> 01:20:05,365
WELL, LET ME SHOW               
YOU HOW TO TAKE OFF             
THE SAFETY, HUH?                


876
01:20:06,369 --> 01:20:08,436
        DAMN.                   


877
01:20:12,775 --> 01:20:14,708
                    I DON'T WANT
                    JAROD HURT. 


878
01:20:14,777 --> 01:20:16,710
    DO MY BEST, SYD.            


879
01:20:16,779 --> 01:20:19,079
        IT'S HOT AND GOOD TO GO.
DAMN.                           


880
01:20:19,148 --> 01:20:21,081
            YOU TAKE THE EAST.  
            GOT THAT?           


881
01:20:21,150 --> 01:20:23,417
    YOU TAKE THE WEST.          
    I'LL FLOAT.                 


882
01:21:19,008 --> 01:21:20,941
[ No Audible Dialogue ]         


883
01:21:27,417 --> 01:21:29,416
    [ No Audible Dialogue ]     


884
01:21:59,615 --> 01:22:01,582
[ No Audible Dialogue ]         


885
01:24:04,273 --> 01:24:06,740
    [ Groaning ]                


886
01:24:20,656 --> 01:24:22,589
        HELLO, JAROD.           


887
01:24:30,266 --> 01:24:33,400
                YOU STOLE ME    
                FROM MY PARENTS.


888
01:24:33,469 --> 01:24:36,770
            YOU HAD THE F.B.I.  
            KILL MY BROTHER.    


889
01:24:36,839 --> 01:24:41,107
AND NOW YOU'RE                  
TRYING TO KILL MY FAMILY.       
WHAT HAVE I EVER DONE TO YOU?   


890
01:24:42,178 --> 01:24:44,878
        YOU EXIST.              


891
01:25:06,302 --> 01:25:08,302
                NO.             


892
01:25:10,706 --> 01:25:14,375
        I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU   
        DO TO ME WHAT YOU DID   
        TO MY BROTHER.          


893
01:25:16,078 --> 01:25:19,646
            YOU LEAVE ME ALONE. 


894
01:25:35,831 --> 01:25:38,131
                    <i> [ Gunshot ]</i>


895
01:25:55,284 --> 01:25:58,786
                <i> [ Groaning ]</i>   


896
01:26:02,958 --> 01:26:05,726
I THOUGHT HE GAVE UP SMOKING.   


897
01:26:07,396 --> 01:26:09,963
            <i> NO. NO, NO, NO.</i>    
            <i> THERE WAS NO PLANT.</i>


898
01:26:10,032 --> 01:26:12,866
        THE INFORMATION         
        ON JAROD'S RENDEZVOUS   
        WITH HIS PARENTS...     


899
01:26:12,935 --> 01:26:16,469
    CAME FROM A PHONE TAP       
    WE'VE HAD ON ST. CATHERINE'S
    FOR OVER 30 YEARS.          


900
01:26:17,606 --> 01:26:21,408
    YES, MR. LYLE.              
    UH, JAROD GOT AWAY, BUT--   


901
01:26:22,878 --> 01:26:26,146
        YOU WANT ME TO COME IN? 
        WHAT FOR?               
        LET'S TALK NOW.         


902
01:26:27,449 --> 01:26:30,918
    WHATEVER YOU SAY.           
    I'LL BE WITH YOU SHORTLY.   


903
01:26:32,121 --> 01:26:34,487
    WE WILL. YOU HAVE MY WORD.  


904
01:26:34,556 --> 01:26:36,556
                THANK--         


905
01:26:39,661 --> 01:26:42,662
    AH. GLAD YOU'RE HERE.       


906
01:26:42,731 --> 01:26:45,732
    REALLY?                     
            OF COURSE.          
            WE HAVE WORK TO DO. 


907
01:26:45,801 --> 01:26:47,868
        WE?                     


908
01:26:47,937 --> 01:26:51,839
    NOW THAT RAINES IS IN       
    DOCTORS' HANDS-- OR GOD'S.  


909
01:26:51,907 --> 01:26:54,041
SKIN GRAFTS CAN BE              
SO DEMANDING.                   


910
01:26:54,109 --> 01:26:57,577
    WELL, AT LEAST              
    HE'LL BE OUT OF YOUR HAIR.  
    ISN'T THAT WHAT YOU WANTED? 


911
01:26:58,914 --> 01:27:01,781
IS THAT WHAT<i> YOU</i> WANTED?        
                HE OVERSTEPPED. 


912
01:27:01,850 --> 01:27:03,851
            I DEALT WITH HIM    
            AS PROMISED.        


913
01:27:03,919 --> 01:27:06,287
THEN WHY WAS HE OUT             
ON THAT STREET YESTERDAY?       


914
01:27:06,355 --> 01:27:09,123
WHY DID HE KNOW                 
RIGHT WHERE JAROD WOULD BE?     


915
01:27:09,192 --> 01:27:11,592
        DIFFICULT FOR A MAN     
        LIKE RAINES TO END UP   
        IN HOSPITAL...          


916
01:27:11,661 --> 01:27:14,794
                WHILE SITTING   
                BEHIND HIS DESK,
                DON'T YOU THINK?


917
01:27:14,863 --> 01:27:17,364
YOU PROMISED ME                 
THAT WE WOULD TALK.             


918
01:27:18,800 --> 01:27:20,734
DID RAINES KILL MOTHER?         


919
01:27:20,802 --> 01:27:22,769
                HONEY. THERE ARE
                NO EASY ANSWERS.


920
01:27:22,838 --> 01:27:26,073
        YES OR NO.              
            <i> ONE DAY YOU'LL</i>     
            <i> UNDERSTAND WHY I--</i> 


921
01:27:26,142 --> 01:27:28,075
    DID HE KILL HER?            


922
01:27:28,144 --> 01:27:32,212
    THERE ARE STILL             
    GREAT REPERCUSSIONS         
    FROM YOUR MOTHER'S DEATH.   


923
01:27:32,281 --> 01:27:35,483
    WHEN I CAN TELL YOU MORE,   
    I WILL.                     


924
01:27:35,551 --> 01:27:39,219
                    <i> TRUST ME.</i>  
                <i> [ Door Opens ]</i> 


925
01:27:39,288 --> 01:27:42,656
                AH, YOU'RE HERE 
                TO ESCORT ME?   


926
01:27:42,724 --> 01:27:45,225
            OF COURSE YOU ARE.  


927
01:27:53,035 --> 01:27:55,001
        <i> [ Mr. Parker Coughs ]</i>  


928
01:28:16,892 --> 01:28:19,660
A FRIEND OF MINE IN CLEANUP     
SENT ME THIS.                   


929
01:28:19,728 --> 01:28:21,762
            BALLISTICS REPORT?  
<i>UH-HUH.</i>                         


930
01:28:21,830 --> 01:28:24,865
WHAT THE HELL'S                 
GOING ON HERE?                  
            I DON'T FOLLOW.     


931
01:28:24,933 --> 01:28:27,868
WELL, THE BULLET THAT           
STRUCK THE OXYGEN TANK--        


932
01:28:27,936 --> 01:28:30,771
THEY CAN'T TELL WHICH GUN       
IT WAS FIRED FROM.              


933
01:28:36,579 --> 01:28:38,579
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>


934
01:28:41,484 --> 01:28:43,483
        HELLO. THIS IS SYDNEY.  


935
01:28:45,021 --> 01:28:48,488
<i>HELLO.</i>                          
<i> HELLO. WHO'S THERE?</i>            


936
01:28:48,558 --> 01:28:50,724
    I MAY BE TIRED, SYDNEY,     


937
01:28:50,793 --> 01:28:52,725
    BUT I'LL NEVER GIVE UP.     


938
01:28:52,794 --> 01:28:55,028
        I DON'T EXPECT YOU TO.  


939
01:28:55,097 --> 01:28:57,097
    I'LL FIND THEM AGAIN.       


940
01:28:57,165 --> 01:28:59,566
    NO ONE IS GOING TO          
    KEEP ME FROM MY FAMILY.     


941
01:28:59,635 --> 01:29:01,901
            I UNDERSTAND.       


942
01:29:01,970 --> 01:29:07,374
        JAROD, YOU WERE CLOSER  
        TO YOUR FAMILY          
        THAN I EVER WAS.        


943
01:29:07,442 --> 01:29:10,076
    I WANT YOU TO BELIEVE THAT. 


944
01:29:10,145 --> 01:29:13,013
    IF IT'S MY FAITH YOU WANT,  


945
01:29:13,081 --> 01:29:15,182
        TELL ME WHERE           
        THEY BURIED MY BROTHER. 


946
01:29:17,319 --> 01:29:20,420
        BURIED HIM?             
                KYLE. YES.      


947
01:29:22,291 --> 01:29:24,691
        - JAROD.                
        - TELL ME, SYDNEY.      


948
01:29:24,760 --> 01:29:27,694
THE VAN'S GAS TANK              
WAS FULL.                       


949
01:29:27,763 --> 01:29:30,730
IT BURNED FOR                   
A VERY LONG TIME.               


950
01:29:30,800 --> 01:29:33,500
NO REMAINS WERE FOUND.          
NOTHING. NADA.                  


951
01:29:33,568 --> 01:29:35,502
                HMM.            


952
01:29:35,570 --> 01:29:38,371
        WHICH IS, YET AGAIN,    
        WHAT YOU LEAVE ME WITH. 


953
01:29:40,375 --> 01:29:43,343
    JAROD. HELLO.               
    ARE YOU STILL THERE?        


954
01:29:43,412 --> 01:29:45,845
            I'M HERE.           


955
01:29:45,915 --> 01:29:48,448
WITH EVERYTHING                 
THAT'S HAPPENED,                


956
01:29:48,517 --> 01:29:51,818
THEY'RE MORE DETERMINED         
THAN EVER TO FIND YOU.          


957
01:29:51,887 --> 01:29:53,954
DO YOU KNOW WHERE YOU'LL GO?    


958
01:29:54,022 --> 01:29:56,823
        I HAVE A GOOD IDEA.     


959
01:29:56,892 --> 01:29:59,459
        CATCH ME IF YOU CAN.    
<i>[ Engines Roaring In Distance ]</i> 


960
01:29:59,528 --> 01:30:01,495
<i>[ Phone Beeps Off ]</i>             


961
01:31:14,704 --> 01:31:15,702
            [ Mews ]            


